WEBVTT

00:01:01.410 --> 00:01:05.290
“番茄大战”凭借约140吨过熟西红柿
And with approximately 140 tons of overripened tomatoes,

00:01:05.290 --> 00:01:09.290
稳居全球最盛大年度食物狂欢
La Tomatina remains the world's greatest annual food fight.

00:01:09.290 --> 00:01:11.370
现在将镜头“扔回”演播室
Throwing it back to you at the studio.

00:01:11.370 --> 00:01:13.750
我们稍后“再酱”
We'll ketchup later.

00:01:15.790 --> 00:01:17.160
这太痛苦了
That was painful.

00:01:17.500 --> 00:01:21.580
怎么 虽然这番茄“梗”没熟 但“藤”鲜的
What? All right, that wasn't my best tomato pun, but it was vine.

00:01:21.580 --> 00:01:23.290
对不对 弗朗西斯
Wasn't it, Francis?

00:01:23.290 --> 00:01:25.830
老大 你不用假装直播
You know, boss, you don't need to give a fake broadcast.

00:01:25.830 --> 00:01:28.740
- 你知道我们是在执行任务吧  - 好吧 淡定
- You know we're on a mission, right? - Okay, easy.

00:01:28.750 --> 00:01:31.410
你有你的办事方法 我有我的 简单
You have your process, I have mine. Simple.

00:01:31.410 --> 00:01:33.740
现在什么也别说了 盯好格拉多夫
Now let's zip it and keep our eyes peeled for Gradov.

00:01:33.750 --> 00:01:37.540
不过话说回来 库珀 我的番茄酱双关是不是还挺好的
Seriously, Coop, the "ketchup" line was strong, yeah?

00:01:37.540 --> 00:01:40.040
诺埃尔 作为你认识最久的朋友
Noel, as your oldest friend,

00:01:40.040 --> 00:01:43.450
我实名认证你的梗一点都不好笑
I can definitively say that was not punny.

00:01:44.700 --> 00:01:48.540
所以我执行重要任务 必须带上你们中情局的人
That's why I don't go big game hunting without you CIA boys.

00:01:48.540 --> 00:01:51.660
说起任务 我们发现了一个可疑人物
Speaking of, we got a lion in the crosshairs.

00:01:52.120 --> 00:01:54.990
灰帽子 灰外套 粉衬衫 朝西南那边去了
Gray hat and jacket, pink shirt, heading southwest,

00:01:55.000 --> 00:01:56.790
与目标描述相符
matching the target's description.

00:01:57.370 --> 00:01:58.950
马上进行面部识别
Walk faces and run it.

00:02:00.200 --> 00:02:02.290
好的 粉衬衫
Okay, pink shirt, pink shirt.

00:02:02.750 --> 00:02:04.450
好了 拍到了
Okay, I got him.

00:02:06.660 --> 00:02:08.540
但我无法确认这就是格拉多夫
But I can't confirm it's Gradov.

00:02:09.000 --> 00:02:10.160
周 你那边有什么发现
Cho, you got anything?

00:02:11.580 --> 00:02:12.620
不行
That's a negative.

00:02:14.080 --> 00:02:15.870
面部识别不出来
No-go for facial recognition.

00:02:18.500 --> 00:02:20.790
等等 他好像就在我眼前
Wait. I think I'm staring right at him.

00:02:21.540 --> 00:02:23.450
离我20英尺 就在你下面 库珀
20 feet from me, right below you, Coop.

00:02:23.450 --> 00:02:24.450
什么
What?

00:02:31.700 --> 00:02:32.910
该死
Ah, shit.

00:02:32.910 --> 00:02:35.740
伙计们 现场有两个 疑似格拉多夫的家伙
Guys, we got two potential Gradovs on site.

00:02:35.750 --> 00:02:36.910
三个
Three.

00:02:38.200 --> 00:02:39.160
该死
Shit.

00:02:39.660 --> 00:02:42.120
他带了诱饵 盯好你那个 杰克斯
He's got decoys in play. Stay on your mark, Jacks.

00:02:45.450 --> 00:02:46.700
报告最新情况 基地
Talk to me, home base.

00:02:46.700 --> 00:02:50.240
面部识别还是不行 他们好像知道我们的摄像头位置
Still no facial recall. It's like they know where our cameras are positioned.

00:02:50.250 --> 00:02:51.870
给我做步态分析
Get me gait analysis.

00:02:51.870 --> 00:02:53.830
我们得申请“梯队监视系统”的补丁
We'd have to request a patch to Echelon.

00:02:53.830 --> 00:02:55.450
那就赶紧申请补丁
Then request the patch!

00:02:58.540 --> 00:02:59.450
亚当斯总监
Director Adams?

00:03:00.250 --> 00:03:02.250
收到要求更新实时补丁的请求
We have a request for a real-time patch.

00:03:02.620 --> 00:03:05.910
军情六处要联合中情局 抓捕一个高价值目标
It's a joint MI6-CIA capture of a high-value target.

00:03:05.910 --> 00:03:08.410
- 有多高  - 国家安全局最高等级
- How high? - NSA priority.

00:03:08.410 --> 00:03:10.330
是俄罗斯军火商维克托格拉多夫
Russian arms dealer Viktor Gradov.

00:03:10.330 --> 00:03:12.080
两年多来第一次发现他的行踪
First sighting in over two years.

00:03:12.750 --> 00:03:15.870
诺埃尔 一号目标仍在西南角
Noel, target one is still in the southwest corner.

00:03:26.000 --> 00:03:27.950
库珀 这辆车感觉不妙
Coop, I don't like this van.

00:03:29.910 --> 00:03:33.410
现场探员 你们被授权连接“梯队”服务器60秒
Field, you're authorized for a 60-second link to Echelon's servers.

00:03:33.410 --> 00:03:35.620
够我锁定真正的格拉多夫了
All the time I need to pin the real Gradov.

00:03:36.370 --> 00:03:39.540
是一辆大众T5 西班牙车牌
It's a VW T5, Spanish plates,

00:03:39.540 --> 00:03:42.870
注册在马德里一家租赁公司名下
registered to a rental company in Madrid.

00:03:43.830 --> 00:03:45.450
你到底是什么东西
What are you?

00:04:11.750 --> 00:04:14.540
现场探员 任务中止 这是陷阱
Field team, abort! We've been set up!

00:05:30.870 --> 00:05:31.910
搞定
Done.

00:05:36.250 --> 00:05:37.120
不许动
Don't move.

00:05:39.450 --> 00:05:40.500
放下
Drop it.

00:07:11.500 --> 00:07:13.240
美国总统威廉德林杰
U.S. President Will Derringer,

00:07:13.250 --> 00:07:15.580
近日国内外支持率持续飙升
amidst soaring popularity at home and abroad,

00:07:15.580 --> 00:07:18.080
已于昨日到达伦敦
touched down in London yesterday.

00:07:18.080 --> 00:07:20.990
德林杰在前往意大利参加北约峰会前
Derringer has stopped in the U.K. for a brief visit

00:07:21.000 --> 00:07:22.990
将对英国进行短暂访问
before he heads to a NATO summit in Italy...

00:07:23.000 --> 00:07:25.240
总统将与执政已六年...
...president will be attending a press

00:07:25.250 --> 00:07:28.740
...但近期深陷困境的英国首相
conference in his first face-to-face meeting

00:07:28.750 --> 00:07:31.490
萨姆克拉克举行首次面对面会晤
with the increasingly embattled  Prime Minister Sam Clarke,

00:07:31.500 --> 00:07:33.580
并共同出席新闻发布会
now serving his sixth year in office...

00:07:33.580 --> 00:07:36.370
德林杰凭借《水蟒》系列电影中 “丹宁毒液”一角
...Derringer smashed worldwide box office records playing the Venom in Denim

00:07:36.370 --> 00:07:40.500
一举打破全球票房纪录
with his Water Cobra franchise.

00:07:42.250 --> 00:07:45.160
然后从枪林弹雨的硬汉形象摇身一变
He then went from bullets flying to tears flowing

00:07:45.160 --> 00:07:48.750
在催人泪下的棒球题材电影 《滑向本垒》中顺利完成银幕转型
with his heartfelt baseball drama Sliding into Home...

00:07:49.540 --> 00:07:50.870
儿子 我们做到了
We did it, son.

00:07:53.410 --> 00:07:54.410
妈妈一定很骄傲
Made Mom proud.

00:07:55.160 --> 00:07:57.080
为他赢得了金球奖提名...
...earning him a Golden Globe nomination...

00:07:57.080 --> 00:07:59.120
上任仅五个月后
After only five months in office,

00:07:59.120 --> 00:08:03.290
德林杰的支持率和选民信任度 就创下历史新高
Derringer is enjoying historic polling numbers and voter confidence.

00:08:03.290 --> 00:08:06.580
在你们的支持下 我们成功征服票房
With your help, we did it at the box office,

00:08:06.580 --> 00:08:09.700
现在我们将征服椭圆办公室
and now we will do it at the Oval Office.

00:08:09.700 --> 00:08:10.790
得了吧
No.

00:08:10.790 --> 00:08:14.580
我们爱威廉

00:08:14.580 --> 00:08:19.370
国家元首

00:08:14.580 --> 00:08:19.370
本WEB版外挂字幕由  风吹来的那片云  双语合并

00:08:21.160 --> 00:08:22.830
早安 首相先生
Good morning, Mr. Prime Minister.

00:08:22.830 --> 00:08:25.290
这是您29号星期四的简报
Here's your brief for Thursday the 29th.

00:08:25.290 --> 00:08:28.830
经济部长将宣布失业率创历史新低
The economic minister will announce record low unemployment.

00:08:28.830 --> 00:08:31.990
波兰的难民危机继续加剧
The refugee crisis in Poland continues to intensify,

00:08:32.000 --> 00:08:34.450
难民人数增加到数万人
with numbers growing into the tens of thousands.

00:08:35.160 --> 00:08:38.540
您原定的早间会议已被取消 以便召开紧急简报会
Your early-morning meetings have been cleared

00:08:38.540 --> 00:08:41.910
通报西班牙境内 以悲剧收场的机密情报行动
for an urgent briefing on a classified intelligence op in Spain that ended in tragedy.

00:08:41.910 --> 00:08:45.620
七名中情局和军情六处特工被杀害
Seven CIA and MI6 operatives have been killed.

00:08:45.620 --> 00:08:50.160
萨姆 很遗憾 诺埃尔比赛特队长失踪了
Sam, I regret to say that team leader Noel Bisset is missing

00:08:50.160 --> 00:08:52.620
据推测已死亡
and presumed dead.

00:08:53.160 --> 00:08:54.450
我很抱歉
I'm so sorry.

00:08:55.040 --> 00:08:57.370
已通知逝者家属
Families of the fallen are being

00:08:57.830 --> 00:08:59.750
会见...
notified...

00:09:00.750 --> 00:09:01.750
你没事吧 老大
You okay, boss?

00:09:15.160 --> 00:09:18.240
在英国王室成员 接待美国总统及其家人之际...
And while the royals play host to the American president and his family,

00:09:19.330 --> 00:09:23.200
...创纪录规模的人群聚集于此 只为目睹威廉德林杰的风采
record crowds are gathered, hoping for a glimpse of Will Derringer,

00:09:23.200 --> 00:09:26.120
证明其在国外和国内一样深受爱戴
proving he's as loved abroad as he is at home.

00:09:28.160 --> 00:09:31.540
我只是不明白 北风和这些有什么关系
I just don't understand what tornado has to do with anything.

00:09:31.540 --> 00:09:34.700
不是北风 是北约 好吗
Not tornados. NATO, okay?

00:09:34.700 --> 00:09:38.200
这些国家就好比一群朋友们
It's like, um, a-a group of friends. Let's say, in this case, countries.

00:09:38.200 --> 00:09:41.290
聚在一起 勾勾小指 承诺有恶霸出现
They-they get together, and they make a pinky promise if they ever see a bully,

00:09:41.290 --> 00:09:44.120
攻击其中一个朋友
let's say this guy, and the bully attacks one of them,

00:09:44.120 --> 00:09:46.660
那他们就必须一起反抗这个恶霸
they all got to join in and stand up to that bully.

00:09:46.660 --> 00:09:49.870
然后他们就开始朝额头扔弹头
And that's when they start dropping warheads on foreheads.

00:09:49.870 --> 00:09:51.410
什么...嘿 什么
Hey, what?

00:09:53.700 --> 00:09:55.200
谁让她看了《水蟒》
Who let her watch Water Cobra?

00:09:55.660 --> 00:09:57.660
- 我在珍妮家看的 - 是吗
- I saw it at Janey's house. - Oh, you did?

00:09:57.660 --> 00:10:01.240
好吧 这下珍妮的妈妈 要接受联邦调查了
Okay, well, Janey's mom is now under federal investigation.

00:10:01.250 --> 00:10:02.410
先生
Sir.

00:10:02.750 --> 00:10:03.580
快走
Scoot.

00:10:08.750 --> 00:10:11.620
- 剑桥大学的讲座是几点  - 4点才开始
- What time's the lecture at Cambridge? - Not till 4:00.

00:10:11.620 --> 00:10:13.870
- 早上在得里雅斯特见  - 好的
- Meet you at Trieste in the morning? - Yeah.

00:10:13.870 --> 00:10:15.370
好好享受吧
Enjoy this.

00:10:15.370 --> 00:10:18.870
趁机和首相搞好关系
And use it as a bonding opportunity with the prime minister.

00:10:19.620 --> 00:10:20.450
拜托
Please.

00:10:20.450 --> 00:10:23.830
别告诉我你还在为炸鱼薯条的事生气
Don't tell me you're still mad about the fish and chips thing.

00:10:23.830 --> 00:10:25.990
他在竞选期间支持了我的对手
He endorsed my opponent in the heat of the campaign.

00:10:26.000 --> 00:10:28.200
他只是和那人吃了个午饭 这可算不上支持
He had lunch with the guy. It's hardly an endorsement.

00:10:28.200 --> 00:10:29.200
不是普通午饭
Wasn't just lunch.

00:10:29.200 --> 00:10:30.620
那可是炸鱼薯条
It was fish and chips.

00:10:30.620 --> 00:10:33.200
你误解他了 萨姆不是坏人
Look, you got off on the wrong foot. Sam's not a bad guy.

00:10:33.200 --> 00:10:34.910
这跟好人坏人没关系
It's not about bad or good.

00:10:34.910 --> 00:10:36.120
他不尊重我
He doesn't respect me.

00:10:38.620 --> 00:10:40.870
你们不是应该说 “没有 他很尊重你”吗
This is where you're supposed to say, "Yes, he does."

00:10:40.870 --> 00:10:42.870
- 他很尊重你 - 太迟了
- He respects you. - Way too late.

00:10:42.870 --> 00:10:44.790
这个从美国人民那里
Is a man who got 83 million votes

00:10:44.790 --> 00:10:47.450
获得8300万张选票的人 得到的尊重难道还不够吗
from the American people not feeling properly respected?

00:10:49.290 --> 00:10:50.410
明天见
See you tomorrow.

00:10:53.540 --> 00:10:56.040
- 你看了演讲稿吗  - 看了 挺好的
- Did you look over your speech? - Yeah. It's solid.

00:10:56.040 --> 00:10:58.120
只要稍加魅力 就能点燃群众的激情
I'll hit it with some fireworks. It'll crackle.

00:10:58.120 --> 00:10:59.490
今天早上应该会很不错
It's gonna be a good morning.

00:10:59.500 --> 00:11:01.120
没那么简单
Won't be that simple.

00:11:01.120 --> 00:11:02.370
说吧
Tell me.

00:11:02.790 --> 00:11:04.620
西班牙的行动失败了
Sideways op, Spain.

00:11:05.950 --> 00:11:07.080
目标是谁
Who was the target?

00:11:07.080 --> 00:11:11.080
维克托格拉多夫 俄罗斯军火商 现已成为极端分子
Viktor Gradov. Russian-born arms dealer turned extremist.

00:11:11.080 --> 00:11:13.080
对 黑市武器开发商
Right. Black market weapons developer

00:11:13.080 --> 00:11:15.790
几年前他搞到了浓缩钚
who got his hands on enriched plutonium a few years back.

00:11:15.790 --> 00:11:17.870
于是我们搞垮了他的生意
Yeah, that's when we took him out of business.

00:11:17.870 --> 00:11:21.290
在北约特遣部队的帮助下 摧毁了他的制造工厂
Destroyed his manufacturing plant with the help of a NATO task force.

00:11:21.290 --> 00:11:24.410
我们发动了空袭 摧毁了他的整个设施
We launched an air strike, destroyed his whole facility.

00:11:24.410 --> 00:11:26.660
在那之后格拉多夫就消失了
After that, Gradov went off the grid.

00:11:27.410 --> 00:11:30.330
西班牙这次行动 是我们这两年首次有机会逮捕他
Spain was our first chance to move on Gradov in two years.

00:11:30.910 --> 00:11:32.080
他现在人在哪
Where is he now?

00:11:32.080 --> 00:11:33.040
不知道
In the wind.

00:11:33.040 --> 00:11:36.370
国安局正在搜查边境入口和机场 想得到点消息
NSA is scraping border entries and airport screenings for noise.

00:11:36.790 --> 00:11:40.040
情报和研究部没有机会做常规分析...
Intelligence and Research didn't have the chance to do their usual analysis.

00:11:40.040 --> 00:11:43.790
该死 要我说多少次  绝不能漏过任何情报
Bloody hell. How many times I've got to say it? We do not leapfrog intel.

00:11:44.700 --> 00:11:45.660
关于诺埃尔
About Noel,

00:11:45.660 --> 00:11:47.370
- 如果你想聊聊... - 不想
- if you want to talk... - I don't.

00:11:48.450 --> 00:11:50.870
我们应该提醒克拉克的团队 注意杰克戈登这个人
We should warn Clarke's team about Jack Gordon.

00:11:50.870 --> 00:11:52.950
杰克喜欢问很尖锐的问题
Jack always goes for the jugular,

00:11:52.950 --> 00:11:55.080
他肯定会揪着西班牙的事穷追猛打
and he will fry us over this Spain thing.

00:11:55.290 --> 00:11:57.040
你跟总统的通讯主管说了
Did you tell the president's comms director

00:11:57.040 --> 00:11:59.120
让他按剧本表演吗
that he must stick to the script?

00:11:59.120 --> 00:12:00.040
说了
Yes.

00:12:00.040 --> 00:12:03.200
很好 希望他别提无法满足的要求
Good. Hopefully he doesn't start writing checks that we can't cash.

00:12:03.200 --> 00:12:07.540
他到现在都还分不清 新闻发布会和媒体宣传会的区别
He still hasn't figured out the difference between a press conference and a press junket.

00:12:09.450 --> 00:12:10.410
首相先生
Mr. Prime Minister.

00:12:10.540 --> 00:12:12.330
- 总统先生 - 你好
- Mr. President. - Yeah.

00:12:12.830 --> 00:12:14.120
我们终于见面了
We finally meet.

00:12:15.290 --> 00:12:17.040
很遗憾你错过了就职典礼
You know, it was a shame that you missed the inauguration.

00:12:17.040 --> 00:12:18.700
真的非常精彩
It was a hell of a show.

00:12:18.950 --> 00:12:20.370
- 那是肯定 - 好吧
- Sure it was. - Yeah.

00:12:21.000 --> 00:12:22.120
这个...
Well...

00:12:23.040 --> 00:12:23.990
我们走吧
Shall we?

00:12:24.000 --> 00:12:25.160
等等
Uh, wait, wait.

00:12:26.830 --> 00:12:30.700
我们应该好好享受这一刻 这是我们的首场二重唱
We should savor this moment. I mean, this is... it's our debut duet.

00:12:31.750 --> 00:12:32.620
“二重唱”
Duet?

00:12:32.620 --> 00:12:34.790
对 就好比我是德瑞博士 而你是阿姆
Yeah. It's like I'm Dr. Dre and you're Eminem,

00:12:34.790 --> 00:12:37.410
这是我们第一次同台演出
and we're taking that stage for the first time together.

00:12:37.410 --> 00:12:38.450
我是阿姆
I'm Eminem?

00:12:41.040 --> 00:12:43.700
对了 关于西班牙的可怕情况
Listen, um, about this terrible situation in Spain.

00:12:44.500 --> 00:12:45.870
如果有记者提问
If it comes up out there,

00:12:45.870 --> 00:12:47.870
我们就避而不谈 把皮球踢给别人
I'd just steer clear of it. Let's just punt it.

00:12:47.870 --> 00:12:49.330
-“踢给别人”  - 没错
- Punt it? - Yeah.

00:12:49.330 --> 00:12:50.370
踢给谁
To where?

00:12:50.620 --> 00:12:52.450
稍后来解决这事的人
Well, to later.

00:12:53.500 --> 00:12:54.870
今天的重点是北约
Today's about NATO,

00:12:54.870 --> 00:12:58.330
- 清洁能源 轻松愉快的话题 -“轻松愉快” 好吧
- clean energy, light and bright stuff. - Light and bright. Okay.

00:12:58.910 --> 00:13:00.910
你想一起热热身吗
You want to warm up together?

00:13:00.910 --> 00:13:03.790
- 做点呼吸练习  - 我这不是在呼吸吗
- Do some breathing exercises? - I'm already breathing.

00:13:03.950 --> 00:13:05.540
- 收到 好吧... - 嗯
- Roger that. Well... - Yeah.

00:13:05.660 --> 00:13:06.870
那就开始我们的表演吧
Let's dance, I guess.

00:13:06.870 --> 00:13:09.160
嘿 就当帮我们俩一个忙
Hey, uh, just do us both a favor out there.

00:13:09.160 --> 00:13:10.950
别让杰克戈登提问
No questions from Jack Gordon.

00:13:11.950 --> 00:13:12.950
好伙计
My guy.

00:13:16.330 --> 00:13:17.830
从今天起
And as of today,

00:13:18.330 --> 00:13:20.790
得益于我们两国共同开发的
thanks to this revolutionary new technology

00:13:20.790 --> 00:13:24.540
这项革命性新技术 我们已成为能源合作伙伴
developed by both of our great nations, we are now partners in energy.

00:13:24.540 --> 00:13:27.910
球床反应堆 不仅是对清洁能源的投资
The pebble-bed reactor is not just an investment in clean energy.

00:13:27.910 --> 00:13:30.330
也是对安全的投资
It's also an investment in security.

00:13:30.330 --> 00:13:33.040
能源安全就是国家安全
Energy security is national security.

00:13:33.040 --> 00:13:35.200
它也是对创造就业的投资
It is also an investment in job creation.

00:13:35.200 --> 00:13:36.910
能提供很多工作机会
A whole lot of jobs.

00:13:36.910 --> 00:13:39.200
我们不再需要与俄罗斯
And we no longer have to deal with the Russians,

00:13:39.200 --> 00:13:40.870
沙特或委内瑞拉在石油问题上打交道
the Saudis or the Venezuelans on oil.

00:13:40.870 --> 00:13:43.910
我们非常期待在接下来的几天内
But we are keen to present this global initiative

00:13:43.910 --> 00:13:47.160
向我们的北约伙伴展示这一全球倡议
to our NATO partners in the coming days.

00:13:47.160 --> 00:13:49.660
好了 问题时间
Okay. Questions?

00:13:50.290 --> 00:13:51.370
德林杰总统
President Derringer!

00:13:51.370 --> 00:13:53.450
《水蟒》刚刚宣布
Uh, it's just been announced that Water Cobra

00:13:53.450 --> 00:13:55.990
将扩展为一个电影宇宙
is being expanded into a cinematic universe.

00:13:56.000 --> 00:13:58.370
你会去客串吗
Any chance you'll be making a cameo?

00:13:58.370 --> 00:14:03.240
各位 我答应过第一夫人 如果我再穿“单宁毒液”的装扮
Oh, folks. I promised the first lady if I ever dressed up as the Venom in Denim again,

00:14:03.250 --> 00:14:06.290
那肯定是在椭圆办公室 或者是为了白宫记者晚宴
it'd either be in the Oval boudoir or for the White House Correspondents' Dinner,

00:14:06.290 --> 00:14:08.410
你只能受邀参加晚宴 椭圆办公室可去不了
and you're only invited to the last one.

00:14:08.870 --> 00:14:10.410
- 克拉克首相 - 请提问
- Prime Minister Clarke. - Yes?

00:14:10.410 --> 00:14:13.040
《每日邮报》刊登了 公爵夫人和其新男友的照片
The Daily Mail have photos of the duchess and a new beau.

00:14:13.040 --> 00:14:16.200
关于你前女友的最新动态 你有何评论
Any comments about your ex-girlfriend's latest escapades?

00:14:16.200 --> 00:14:18.990
- 好吧 谁有真正的问题  - 等一下
- Okay. Who has a real question? - Hey, hold on a minute.

00:14:19.000 --> 00:14:22.200
还有谁不想让首相继续打光棍了
Now, who else is tired of seeing the prime minister as a single man?

00:14:22.200 --> 00:14:24.870
我们给他定制一季《单身汉》吧
I'll tell you what. How about we get him his own season of The Bachelor?

00:14:24.870 --> 00:14:27.000
- 还有谁想加入  - 好啊 搞起来
- Who's with me? - Yeah! Let's do it!

00:14:28.790 --> 00:14:29.660
杰克戈登
Jack Gordon.

00:14:31.870 --> 00:14:34.990
今天早上在西班牙 有六名英国人和美国人死亡
There are six dead British and Americans in Spain this morning.

00:14:35.000 --> 00:14:38.990
您能否就抓捕 著名军火商维克托格拉多夫的
Can you comment on speculation this is the result

00:14:39.000 --> 00:14:41.750
秘密行动失败的猜测发表评论
of a failed covert operation to capture known arms dealer Viktor Gradov?

00:14:42.830 --> 00:14:45.740
秘密行动之所以是秘密 是有原因的
Covert operations are covert for a reason.

00:14:45.750 --> 00:14:47.700
其他的无可奉告
That's all I'm gonna say on that.

00:14:47.700 --> 00:14:50.330
不仅如此 格拉多夫会后悔 昨天没有束手就擒
That and Gradov's gonna wish we caught him yesterday.

00:14:50.330 --> 00:14:52.410
因为当我们抓到他的时候
Because when we do get our hands on him,

00:14:52.410 --> 00:14:54.740
他就会知道复仇
he is going to be forming a special relationship

00:14:54.750 --> 00:14:56.990
到底是什么滋味
with the concept of retribution.

00:14:57.000 --> 00:15:00.200
我们还应将此 作为一个集体反思的时刻
We should also be using this as a collective moment of introspection,

00:15:00.200 --> 00:15:03.040
找出哪里出了问题 并从中吸取教训
find out what went wrong and learn from it.

00:15:03.040 --> 00:15:05.660
有消息称 行动期间访问了“梯队系统”
Leaks indicate that Echelon was accessed during the op.

00:15:05.660 --> 00:15:10.240
你是否准备好承认 有这么一个秘密监视系统
Are you ready to acknowledge the existence of a top secret surveillance program

00:15:10.250 --> 00:15:12.990
监控着我们所有的邮件 视频会议
which monitors all of our emails, video conferences,

00:15:13.000 --> 00:15:14.700
- 还有电话... - 汤姆
- phone calls... - Tom.

00:15:14.700 --> 00:15:17.740
我不能一直说“无可奉告”
There's only so many times I can say "no comment" to that.

00:15:17.750 --> 00:15:18.990
所以我来回答
I'll comment.

00:15:19.000 --> 00:15:21.200
我们的敌人应该感到害怕
Our enemies should be afraid.

00:15:21.200 --> 00:15:23.540
我们有这样的工具和技术
We have the tools and we have the technology

00:15:23.540 --> 00:15:25.490
如果他们胆敢进犯 我们就能找到并摧毁他们
to find and destroy them if they challenge us.

00:15:25.500 --> 00:15:27.290
我们会做出以下承诺
We aren't making any promises except that

00:15:27.290 --> 00:15:30.950
我们将不懈努力以取得成果
we will work tirelessly to get results.

00:15:30.950 --> 00:15:31.990
没错
Well, we are.

00:15:32.000 --> 00:15:34.870
美利坚合众国在此承诺 一定会取得成果
The United States of America is promising results.

00:15:34.870 --> 00:15:36.700
德林杰总统 你有什么话要对
President Derringer,

00:15:36.700 --> 00:15:39.450
在西班牙遇害者的家人们说吗
do you have a message for the families of the men and women killed in Spain?

00:15:39.450 --> 00:15:42.160
我在特种部队待过很长时间
I've spent a lot of time with Special Forces.

00:15:42.160 --> 00:15:43.240
和他们一起训练
Trained with them,

00:15:43.250 --> 00:15:44.410
从他们身上学习
learned from them.

00:15:44.410 --> 00:15:48.450
我要说的是 我们必须做得更好 我们也一定能做得更好
And what I have to say is we must do better. We will do better.

00:15:48.450 --> 00:15:53.790
当你说“和他们一起训练” 是指为了电影角色训练吧
When you say, um, "trained with them," that was for an acting role, yes?

00:15:53.790 --> 00:15:56.790
- 是的 但是... - 我是说 你从来没服过役
- Yes, but, uh... - I mean, y-you've never served.

00:15:56.790 --> 00:16:00.620
作为一个在英国军队服役的人 你们都知道
As someone who did serve in the British Army, as most of you know,

00:16:00.620 --> 00:16:03.040
如果我对家属有话要说
if I did have something to say to the families,

00:16:03.040 --> 00:16:06.910
我会当面跟他们说 而不会通过你向英雄致敬 杰克
I would say it to them directly. I do not salute heroes through you, Jack.

00:16:06.910 --> 00:16:08.870
说实话 你没上过战场
To be clear, you never saw combat.

00:16:08.870 --> 00:16:11.080
恕我直言 先生们 你们是政客
But with all due respect, gentlemen, you're politicians.

00:16:11.080 --> 00:16:15.790
你们不会真把自己当成真英雄了吧
You don't equate yourselves with actual heroes, do you?

00:16:20.540 --> 00:16:22.620
真是糟透了
Well, that was a shit-bath.

00:16:22.620 --> 00:16:26.370
社交媒体上热议不断 #指挥官之争 正登上热搜
Socials are lighting up. Hashtag "commanders in beef" is trending.

00:16:26.370 --> 00:16:27.580
该死
Goddamn it!

00:16:28.370 --> 00:16:31.040
你很清楚杰克戈登是个麻烦 我警告过你的
You knew Jack Gordon was trouble. I warned you.

00:16:31.040 --> 00:16:33.790
我的地盘 我想让谁提问就让谁提问
My town. I'll call on whomever I want.

00:16:34.450 --> 00:16:35.500
休息五分钟
Let's take five.

00:16:37.080 --> 00:16:38.910
我可不怕媒体
You know, I'm not afraid of the press.

00:16:38.910 --> 00:16:41.990
不是每个人都需要被所有人喜欢
Not all of us have a compulsive need to be liked by everyone.

00:16:42.000 --> 00:16:43.490
恕我直言...
With all due respect...

00:16:43.500 --> 00:16:45.790
我知道你乐于替他出头
I know you like to fight his battles for him, Simone.

00:16:45.790 --> 00:16:47.870
你的总统任期才刚开始
Your presidency is in diapers.

00:16:47.870 --> 00:16:49.330
你还在学习中
You're on a learning curve.

00:16:49.830 --> 00:16:53.200
- 我干这行已经六年了 - 你 我能替自己出头
- I've been on this slog for six years. - You? I fight my own battles.

00:16:53.200 --> 00:16:55.160
要不拿数据说话 要不先从
You, you want to talk numbers?

00:16:55.160 --> 00:16:56.790
你的支持率开始说起
Your approval ratings, that's a great place to start.

00:16:57.750 --> 00:17:01.160
不像你 我要的是结果 而不是别人在Ins上给我点赞
Unlike you, I'll take results over likes on Instagram.

00:17:02.120 --> 00:17:06.120
你都不在乎别人怎么想 你还要求大家集体反思一下
You-you clearly don't care about what people think. You called for a collective moment of introspection?

00:17:06.120 --> 00:17:09.290
这么说吧 我更关心 民众如何还得起抵押贷款
Let's just say I'm more concerned with how people pay their mortgages

00:17:09.290 --> 00:17:10.990
如何送孩子上大学
and send their kids to university.

00:17:11.000 --> 00:17:14.910
是啊 公众最爱看 政客们给他们布置“家庭作业”了
Oh, for sure, 'cause God knows there's nothing the public loves more than politicians giving them homework.

00:17:14.910 --> 00:17:18.160
你是在为炸鱼薯条那事生气吗  如果是的话就直说吧
Is this about the fish and chips thing? 'Cause if it is, just say it.

00:17:18.160 --> 00:17:20.370
我一点也没为这破事生气
I am not mad about the goddamn fish and chips thing.

00:17:20.370 --> 00:17:22.830
够了 你们俩今天都表现得不怎么样
Enough. Neither of you were at your best today.

00:17:22.830 --> 00:17:25.790
同意 我们得尽快解决这事
Agreed. We need to give this a short shelf life.

00:17:25.790 --> 00:17:27.910
他说得对 改变说话方式
He's right. Change the narrative.

00:17:27.910 --> 00:17:29.620
把这变成一个机会...
Turn this into an opportunity.

00:17:29.620 --> 00:17:31.910
证明你们是团结的
To show that you guys are united.

00:17:32.870 --> 00:17:33.950
我知道了
I've got it.

00:17:33.950 --> 00:17:35.830
你们一起飞去得里雅斯特
You fly to Trieste together

00:17:36.160 --> 00:17:37.410
搭乘空军一号
on Air Force One.

00:17:38.250 --> 00:17:39.750
我不确定飞机坐不坐得下
I don't know if we have enough room.

00:17:39.870 --> 00:17:41.620
不用 我不坐 感谢你的好意
No, I'm good, thank you very much.

00:17:41.620 --> 00:17:44.410
- 而且我今晚必须去华沙 - 不 听我说完
- And besides, I have to be in Warsaw tonight. - Hear me out, all right?

00:17:44.410 --> 00:17:48.540
你们俩在伦敦的飞机舷梯上停留35秒 挥手微笑
You both do 35 seconds on the airstairs here in London, waving and smiling,

00:17:48.540 --> 00:17:51.040
在华沙短暂停留下 你们早餐前就能到达得里雅斯特
pit stop in Warsaw. You'll be in Trieste by breakfast.

00:17:51.040 --> 00:17:54.950
到那时 你们在舷梯上的照片 那团结一致的景象
By that time, pictures of you on those airstairs, a vision of solidarity,

00:17:55.450 --> 00:17:58.750
将会登上全球十份报纸中的八份头版
will be on the front page of eight out of ten newspapers all around the world.

00:18:01.200 --> 00:18:02.160
昆西
Quincy.

00:18:02.750 --> 00:18:03.830
布拉德肖
Bradshaw.

00:18:04.830 --> 00:18:07.990
我是美国总统 我不和任何人共用舞台
I am the President of the United States. I don't share the stage with anyone.

00:18:08.000 --> 00:18:10.490
搭便车 这就是你的解决方案
Hitch a ride? Is that your solution?

00:18:10.500 --> 00:18:12.620
这样民意调查中的支持率 必将提升三个百分点
It's a guaranteed three-point bump in the polls.

00:18:12.620 --> 00:18:14.950
听着 我们的任期刚开始
Look, we are in the early days.

00:18:14.950 --> 00:18:17.080
你得证明你能交到朋友
You've got to show you can make friends.

00:18:17.080 --> 00:18:19.450
眼下 我们更需要他 而非他需要我们
Right now we need him more than he needs us.

00:18:20.540 --> 00:18:22.660
萨姆 为了胜利
Sam, take the win.

00:18:23.450 --> 00:18:24.830
坐他的飞机吧
Take the flight.

00:18:24.830 --> 00:18:26.080
你一起吗
Will you be there?

00:18:26.700 --> 00:18:28.250
我跟先遣队一起
I'll go with the advance team.

00:18:29.250 --> 00:18:32.040
昆西和我会确保 得里雅斯特的跑道边挤满媒体
Quincy and I will foam the runway with the press in Trieste.

00:18:34.870 --> 00:18:36.290
首相先生
Mr. Prime Minister.

00:18:38.750 --> 00:18:42.160
能否请你赏脸 和我一起乘坐空军一号
Would you do me the honor and fly with me aboard Air Force One?

00:18:52.120 --> 00:18:53.040
说实话...
I'll be honest.

00:18:54.290 --> 00:18:55.580
我整晚睡不着在想
It kept me up all night.

00:18:57.040 --> 00:19:00.540
为什么我花重金 请来最顶尖的狙击手
How is it that I hire the best sniper money can buy

00:19:00.540 --> 00:19:02.410
结果他偏偏在关键时刻失手了
and he misses the one shot meant to protect

00:19:02.410 --> 00:19:04.490
没能护住我整个行动中最重要的人
the most important man in my entire operation?

00:19:04.500 --> 00:19:07.490
好吧 谢谢 但我们都在尽自己的职责
Yeah, thanks, but we're all just doing our part.

00:19:07.500 --> 00:19:10.000
都是拼图的碎片 被子上的补丁
Pieces of a puzzle, patches on a quilt...

00:19:16.790 --> 00:19:18.830
我先以为是设备故障
I assumed it was faulty equipment.

00:19:20.000 --> 00:19:22.830
现在我知道了 是人为失误
But now I know it was human error.

00:19:23.620 --> 00:19:24.620
就像你说的...
Like you say...

00:19:29.870 --> 00:19:32.540
“发生的一切都是最好的安排”
"Everything that happens happens for the best."

00:19:33.160 --> 00:19:34.120
是啊
Yes.

00:19:37.700 --> 00:19:38.580
来吧
Come.

00:19:39.250 --> 00:19:40.080
坐
Sit down.

00:19:42.330 --> 00:19:46.000
我妈妈很喜欢这句话
My mother was very fond of that phrase.

00:19:46.950 --> 00:19:50.490
她是个格达尔卡 算命的
She was a gadalka. A fortune teller.

00:19:50.500 --> 00:19:52.040
她会看茶叶
She read tea leaves.

00:19:52.870 --> 00:19:54.450
她能看到未来
She could see the future.

00:19:55.500 --> 00:19:57.830
她看到了我的未来 说有一天
She saw mine and said that one day

00:19:57.830 --> 00:19:59.870
我会受到非常不公正的待遇
I would be served a great injustice,

00:20:00.330 --> 00:20:03.870
我人生的目标 就是让那些责任人付出代价
and it would be my mission in life to punish those responsible.

00:20:04.250 --> 00:20:06.830
没有任何事 任何人
And nothing or no one

00:20:07.620 --> 00:20:08.910
能阻止我
would get in my way.

00:20:24.160 --> 00:20:26.740
十多年来 美国总统首次...
It's been over a decade since a U.S. president

00:20:28.160 --> 00:20:30.700
...在空军一号上接待英国首相
has hosted a British prime minister on Air Force One,

00:20:30.700 --> 00:20:34.040
这次访问必将载入史册
making this trip one for the history books.

00:20:34.620 --> 00:20:35.580
瞧瞧啊
Check her out.

00:20:35.580 --> 00:20:37.080
刚下生产线
Fresh off the assembly line.

00:20:37.080 --> 00:20:39.290
这款飞机的翼展 比前代型号宽了30英尺
30-foot wider wingspan than the previous model.

00:20:39.290 --> 00:20:41.620
速度可以突破音速 转弯时像F-15战斗机一样灵活
Can break Mach 1, oh, and corners like an F-15.

00:20:41.620 --> 00:20:43.830
很惊讶你没有在它侧面画火焰
Surprised you didn't paint flames on the side of it.

00:20:43.830 --> 00:20:46.700
你这是在嫉妒 你的飞机很烂 而且名字也不酷
Ah, you're just jealous 'cause your plane sucks and doesn't have a cool name.

00:20:46.700 --> 00:20:47.700
伙计们
Fellas.

00:20:50.040 --> 00:20:52.040
我们爱威廉
We love Will! We love Will!

00:21:22.830 --> 00:21:24.290
首相先生
Mr. Prime Minister.

00:21:24.290 --> 00:21:25.660
我听说你喜欢黑麦威士忌
I heard you like rye.

00:21:26.500 --> 00:21:28.870
这款酒来自我的家乡肯塔基
This one comes from my hometown in Kentucky.

00:21:32.870 --> 00:21:36.410
这就是美国独特性与优越性的体现
Now, that is American exceptionalism in action.

00:21:37.450 --> 00:21:38.290
谢谢
Thank you.

00:21:38.290 --> 00:21:39.660
请慢用 先生
Enjoy, sir.

00:22:03.330 --> 00:22:05.000
他在这呢 来这边
There he is. Come on.

00:22:08.750 --> 00:22:11.540
跟克拉克首相打个招呼
Say hello to Prime Minister Clarke. Hey.

00:22:11.540 --> 00:22:13.950
对他好点 他最喜欢哈里斯泰尔斯了
Be nice to him, Sawyer. He's besties with Harry Styles.

00:22:13.950 --> 00:22:16.370
我不太确定 但如果他下次去华盛顿
Well, I don't know about that, but next time he's in Washington,

00:22:16.370 --> 00:22:18.120
我看看能不能给你弄到个好座位
I'll see if I can get you some good seats.

00:22:18.120 --> 00:22:19.330
- 谢谢 - 谢谢
- Thank you. - Thank you.

00:22:19.330 --> 00:22:21.620
很高兴终于见到你 首相先生
Nice to finally meet you, Mr. Prime Minister.

00:22:21.620 --> 00:22:23.370
不必 说实话 叫我萨姆就好
Now, honestly, just-just call me Sam.

00:22:23.370 --> 00:22:25.330
很遗憾这次没能见面
I'm so sorry we missed each other.

00:22:25.330 --> 00:22:28.290
你们俩照顾好自己 对他好一点 萨姆
You two take care of yourselves, and go easy on him, Sam.

00:22:28.290 --> 00:22:30.080
我们还在学习
We're still learning the ropes.

00:22:30.080 --> 00:22:32.910
- 我会尽量让他远离麻烦 - 好了 嘿
- I'll try and keep him out of trouble. - Okay, hey.

00:22:32.910 --> 00:22:34.830
爱你们 明天再聊
Love you guys. Talk to you tomorrow.

00:22:37.620 --> 00:22:38.750
你很擅长这个
You're good at that.

00:22:39.660 --> 00:22:40.950
擅长什么
Good at what?

00:22:40.950 --> 00:22:42.490
做正常人...
Being normal. Ish.

00:22:42.500 --> 00:22:45.040
- 接近正常 - 我该说谢谢
Uh, thank you?

00:22:45.410 --> 00:22:47.910
你应该更经常地 向人们展示你的这一面
You should show people that side of you more often.

00:22:47.910 --> 00:22:49.620
第一步是结束单身
Start by ditching the bachelor status.

00:22:49.620 --> 00:22:51.620
世界领导人如果未婚会让人不安
World leader who's unmarried?

00:22:51.620 --> 00:22:53.290
留给人们太多想象空间
Freaks people out, leaves too much to the imagination.

00:22:53.290 --> 00:22:54.790
他们会想象什么
What are they imagining?

00:22:54.790 --> 00:22:56.740
我不确定 类似《大开眼戒》里那种派对
I don't know, Eyes Wide Shut parties

00:22:56.750 --> 00:22:59.990
或者到了晚上你就成了蒙面义警 做一些奇怪的 令人不安的事
or by night you're some masked vigilante into some weird, unsettling shit.

00:23:00.000 --> 00:23:02.450
听着 人们想要的是确切性
Look, people want clarity.

00:23:02.450 --> 00:23:04.990
婚姻能提供一种确切性 能让你的形象显得更亲切
Marriage gives them clarity. It softens the image.

00:23:05.000 --> 00:23:07.160
我搞糊涂了 你是在给我建议
I'm confused. Are you giving me advice

00:23:07.160 --> 00:23:10.120
还是在向我推荐你的烂情景喜剧
or are you pitching me on one of your shit rom-coms?

00:23:10.120 --> 00:23:12.290
我懂 你不喜欢我的电影
All right, I get it. You don't like my movies.

00:23:12.290 --> 00:23:13.990
我从没看过你的电影
I've never seen your movies.

00:23:14.000 --> 00:23:16.910
因为萨姆克拉克不喜欢娱乐
Because Sam Clarke is the man who does not like to be entertained.

00:23:16.910 --> 00:23:19.830
不 是因为我喜欢真正的电影
No, it's 'cause I like actual cinema.

00:23:19.830 --> 00:23:23.080
拜托 难道是我不想 和韦斯安德森或奉俊昊合作吗
Come on. You don't think I wanted to work with Wes Anderson or Bong Joon Ho?

00:23:23.080 --> 00:23:24.580
我当然想
Of course I do.

00:23:24.580 --> 00:23:25.910
我受过正统训练
I'm classically trained.

00:23:25.910 --> 00:23:27.910
你知道我和爱德华诺顿演过戏吗
Did you know I once did a play with Edward Norton?

00:23:29.620 --> 00:23:33.120
但老天爷一直说我拿枪会很帅
But the universe keeps telling me I look cool with a gun in my hand.

00:23:34.120 --> 00:23:35.000
玩具枪
A toy gun.

00:23:40.500 --> 00:23:41.500
你是怎么回事
What is it with you?

00:23:42.370 --> 00:23:45.240
一天到晚觉得自己比别人都强
Walking around, thinking you're better than everybody else.

00:23:45.250 --> 00:23:48.370
一开始我以为是英国人都这样 现在我明白了 只有你这样
First, thought it was a British thing. Then I realized it's a you thing.

00:23:48.370 --> 00:23:50.660
我认识保罗麦卡特尼 好吗
I know Paul McCartney, okay?

00:23:50.660 --> 00:23:52.660
他比你受欢迎多了
He's put a whole lot more wins on the board than you,

00:23:52.660 --> 00:23:54.200
而且他酷毙了
and he is cool as shit!

00:23:58.200 --> 00:24:00.450
- 要我送过去吗  - 我送就行 谢谢
- Want me to take it up? - I got it. Thanks.

00:24:02.500 --> 00:24:06.240
你知道吗 我不会 因为想要被喜欢或被爱而道歉
And you know what? I'm not gonna apologize for wanting to be liked or loved.

00:24:06.250 --> 00:24:08.950
我们很幸运 干着世上最非凡的两份工作
We're blessed with two of the most extraordinary jobs ever created,

00:24:08.950 --> 00:24:12.700
这份工作的一部分 就是灌输希望 让人们感觉美好
and part of that job is to instill hope. It's to make people feel good.

00:24:12.700 --> 00:24:17.370
但是根据我的经验 希望最终只会带来失望
Yeah, well, based on my experience, okay, hope is just delayed disappointment.

00:24:17.370 --> 00:24:20.660
希望既填不饱肚子 也遮不了风雨
Doesn't put food on the table. Doesn't put a roof over anyone's head.

00:24:20.660 --> 00:24:23.120
如果你只想着如何让人们感觉美好
And if you want to focus on making people "feel good,"

00:24:23.120 --> 00:24:25.450
那你就永远无法理解如何帮助他们
then you're never gonna understand how to help them.

00:24:25.450 --> 00:24:29.620
你是总司令 不是拉斯维加斯的DJ
You are the commander in chief. You're not some DJ in Vegas.

00:24:29.620 --> 00:24:31.910
我的职位头衔用不着你提醒
I don't need to be refreshed on my job title.

00:24:31.910 --> 00:24:33.160
我们把话说清楚
Let's be clear about that.

00:24:40.250 --> 00:24:42.450
别告诉机长我偷了他的藏货给你们
Don't tell the captain I snuck you his stash.

00:24:42.450 --> 00:24:43.410
多谢
Thanks.

00:25:09.000 --> 00:25:10.370
前往拦截
Move to intercept.

00:25:17.870 --> 00:25:20.200
要知道 等你的蜜月期结束
Just know, once this honeymoon period is over,

00:25:20.200 --> 00:25:22.740
你的未来只会让你失望
there is only disappointment in your future,

00:25:22.750 --> 00:25:26.040
因为这份工作 我的工作 就是受苦
because this job, my job, is about suffering.

00:25:26.040 --> 00:25:29.490
是吗 预言家先生 等那天真来了 咱俩倒是可以坐下来
Yeah, Nostradamus? When that day comes, maybe then you and I can sit down

00:25:29.500 --> 00:25:31.370
好好聊一聊炸鱼薯条
and talk about it over some fish and chips.

00:25:32.250 --> 00:25:34.540
我就知道你迟早会说真话 果然如此
I knew the truth would come out. There it is.

00:25:34.700 --> 00:25:37.490
真棒 你成功了 阿加莎克里斯蒂破案了
Oh, great. You did it, Agatha Christie. You cracked the case.

00:25:37.500 --> 00:25:40.580
- 给大家奖励点史酷比饼干吧 - 威廉 翻篇吧
- Let's give Scooby Snacks to everybody. - Will, let it go.

00:25:40.580 --> 00:25:43.700
你大白天在莱塞特广场正中央
You took my opponent for fish and chips in broad daylight

00:25:43.700 --> 00:25:46.740
请我的竞争对手吃炸鱼薯条 你明知道那里全是摄影师
in the middle of "Liester" Square, and you knew photographers would be there!

00:25:46.750 --> 00:25:48.540
是莱斯特广场
First of all, it's pronounced Leicester Square.

00:25:48.540 --> 00:25:50.790
别闹了 他是老朋友 我只是带他去吃午饭
And, no, bollocks, he's an old friend. I took him for lunch.

00:25:50.790 --> 00:25:52.410
你明知道这会引人遐想
You knew there were political implications.

00:25:52.410 --> 00:25:55.540
又不是人人都能仰仗 议会中剑桥精英集团的政治资源
Not all of us have some posh Cambridge Mafia in Parliament

00:25:55.540 --> 00:25:56.910
赢得选举
helping us get elected!

00:25:58.160 --> 00:26:00.370
我拼了命才走到这里
I busted my ass to get to where I am.

00:26:00.370 --> 00:26:01.950
我出生于政府公屋社区
I was born in a housing estate

00:26:01.950 --> 00:26:05.080
从未享有任何特权资源
and was never given anything on a silver platter.

00:26:05.080 --> 00:26:08.660
为了交剑桥的学费 我打了三份工 然后又去参军
I worked three jobs to pay for Cambridge,

00:26:08.660 --> 00:26:11.080
然后开始社区组织工作 继而担任国防武官职务
and then to the Army, and then to community organizing,

00:26:11.080 --> 00:26:15.080
我是一步步从议会基层爬上来的 懂吗 不是所有人搞政治
and then Defence Attaché, and worked my way up through Parliament. Now, not all of us got our political start

00:26:15.080 --> 00:26:18.450
都靠经纪公司看上 你那副“大兵乔”的帅脸
because some commercial agent decided they like our G.I. Joe jawline!

00:26:18.450 --> 00:26:19.370
注意你的语言
Watch it!

00:26:19.500 --> 00:26:22.910
你从内裤模特混到走红毯
No, no, no! You went from modeling your underwear to being on the red carpet

00:26:22.910 --> 00:26:25.330
一直到摸到核按钮
to having your finger on the nuclear button,

00:26:25.330 --> 00:26:28.000
连一天基层都没干过
all without doing a single day of public service!

00:26:28.120 --> 00:26:31.040
说真的 伙计 看到你在这扮总统
So, yes, mate, when I see you play the role of president,

00:26:31.040 --> 00:26:33.620
我恶心得都要吐了 你就会念台词
it makes me sick to my stomach, because you know your lines--

00:26:33.620 --> 00:26:35.040
你可太会了
oh, yes, you do--

00:26:35.040 --> 00:26:37.040
但总统这个角色你可演不来
but you're not believable in the part.

00:26:37.040 --> 00:26:39.990
我要是能给你对手站台 早站了
And if I could've endorsed your opponent, yes, I would've,

00:26:40.000 --> 00:26:42.740
至少这样白宫里会有一个真领袖
because at least there'd be a real leader in the White House

00:26:42.750 --> 00:26:45.830
而不是个丢人现眼 只会爆米花政治的戏精总统
and not some embarrassing, bullshit, popcorn president!

00:26:45.830 --> 00:26:47.410
- 什么  - 你听到我说的了
- What's that? - You heard what I said!

00:26:47.410 --> 00:26:48.540
不是 那是什么
No, what's that?

00:26:55.700 --> 00:26:57.790
先生们 待在办公室 保证自己安全
Sirs, secure yourselves in the office. Fasten your seatbelts.

00:27:00.290 --> 00:27:03.160
系好安全带 先生 请坐下
Sir. Take your seat, please.

00:27:04.700 --> 00:27:05.660
发生什么了
What's happening?

00:27:05.660 --> 00:27:08.080
不明航空器 你已进入限制空域
Unidentified aircraft, you're in restricted airspace.

00:27:08.080 --> 00:27:10.700
立即转向撤离 否则将遭火力拦截
Pull away immediately or you will be fired upon.

00:27:10.700 --> 00:27:11.740
全频段无线电失效
All radios are out.

00:27:11.750 --> 00:27:13.200
所有通讯全部中断
Comms are fried across the board.

00:27:26.000 --> 00:27:26.830
天啊
Dear God.

00:27:27.540 --> 00:27:29.580
- 准备武器 - 是 长官
- Ready the weapons. - Yes, sir.

00:27:33.790 --> 00:27:34.790
大事不妙
Oh, shit.

00:27:49.290 --> 00:27:50.120
先生们
Uh, gentlemen.

00:27:52.870 --> 00:27:54.410
被多枚武器锁定
Multiple inbound bogies!

00:27:54.410 --> 00:27:55.700
开火
Open fire!

00:28:09.830 --> 00:28:11.330
总统先生 先生
Mr. President! Sir!

00:28:11.870 --> 00:28:13.250
这是怎么回事
What the hell's going on?

00:28:18.540 --> 00:28:19.370
该死
Shit.

00:28:19.370 --> 00:28:21.910
我们得去飞机后部 快走
We got to get to the back of the plane! Go! Go! Go!

00:28:32.120 --> 00:28:33.370
别再射无人机了
Stop shooting the drones!

00:28:33.370 --> 00:28:34.870
快射飞机
Shoot the goddamn plane!

00:28:55.410 --> 00:28:56.410
抓紧了
Hold on!

00:28:58.040 --> 00:29:01.620
紧急下降至10000英尺 以稳定舱内压力
Initiating emergency descent to 10,000 for cabin pressure stabilization.

00:29:11.790 --> 00:29:14.620
走 后面有降落伞
Let's go! There are parachutes in the back!

00:29:17.410 --> 00:29:19.290
又来了一波
Here comes another wave.

00:29:36.250 --> 00:29:37.660
二号引擎失灵
We lost engine two.

00:29:37.790 --> 00:29:39.080
准备压杆操作
Gonna lean into it.

00:29:56.370 --> 00:29:57.870
快 我们得跳过去
Come on, we got to jump!

00:30:02.200 --> 00:30:04.120
那边 穿过门
That way! Through the door!

00:30:08.950 --> 00:30:10.250
快 先生 快走
Come on, sir! Move!

00:30:11.450 --> 00:30:12.500
正在改平
We're leveling out.

00:30:17.000 --> 00:30:18.250
他们完蛋了
They're finished.

00:30:18.790 --> 00:30:19.830
我们回家吧
Let's go home.

00:30:32.370 --> 00:30:33.620
走
Let's go!

00:30:40.000 --> 00:30:42.700
快点 快走 快
Come on! Let's move! Quick!

00:30:50.040 --> 00:30:52.080
这两个应该能用
These two should be intact.

00:30:54.410 --> 00:30:57.870
该死 我们要落在白俄罗斯领空
Shit! We're going down in Belarusian airspace.

00:30:58.000 --> 00:31:00.450
你们得去我们在波兰的安全屋
You'll need to get to our safe house in Poland.

00:31:00.450 --> 00:31:03.870
跳出去后使劲拉手柄 剩下的就交给降落伞
Rip it hard once you're out. The chute'll do the rest.

00:31:03.870 --> 00:31:05.160
你跟我用一个伞
We can double up.

00:31:05.160 --> 00:31:06.830
不行 太冒险了
Not a chance. Too risky.

00:31:06.830 --> 00:31:08.160
那这些人怎么办
What about all these people?

00:31:08.160 --> 00:31:09.830
我们都有自己的职责
We all have our jobs to do.

00:31:09.830 --> 00:31:11.500
你们的职责就是活下去
Yours is to survive.

00:31:14.830 --> 00:31:19.410
去华沙格达通斯克大桥下面的 金山矿业公司
Get to Golden Mountain Mining Company under the Gdanski Bridge in Warsaw.

00:31:19.410 --> 00:31:21.080
先生们 重复一遍
Let me hear it, sirs.

00:31:21.410 --> 00:31:23.000
金山矿业公司
Golden Mountain Mining Company.

00:31:23.200 --> 00:31:24.450
格达通斯克大桥
Gdanski Bridge!

00:31:26.200 --> 00:31:28.200
我很荣幸 总统先生
It's been an honor, Mr. President.

00:31:49.200 --> 00:31:50.700
该死
Oh, shit.

00:32:15.950 --> 00:32:19.160
我们刚刚收到一段令人震惊的影像
We have just received devastating footage

00:32:19.160 --> 00:32:21.790
显示空军一号在白俄罗斯西部坠毁
of Air Force One going down over Western Belarus.

00:32:21.790 --> 00:32:26.040
威廉姆德林杰总统 和萨缪尔克拉克首相
President William Derringer and Prime Minister Samuel Clarke...

00:32:26.040 --> 00:32:28.620
据推测已遇难
are presumed dead.

00:32:29.830 --> 00:32:33.620
我们正等待五角大楼 就事故潜在原因或嫌疑人发表声明
We're awaiting word from the Pentagon on the potential cause or suspects.

00:32:34.290 --> 00:32:38.000
目前尚无组织宣称 对这起悲剧性事件负责
No groups are claiming responsibility for this tragic loss.

00:32:38.120 --> 00:32:42.410
议会正召开紧急会议商讨继任方案
An emergency session of Parliament is convening to discuss succession strategy,

00:32:42.410 --> 00:32:45.240
片刻前 伊丽莎白科克副总统
while moments ago V.P. Elizabeth Kirk was sworn in

00:32:45.250 --> 00:32:48.080
在意大利得里雅斯特 宣誓就任代理总统
as acting president in Trieste, Italy.

00:32:48.250 --> 00:32:51.540
当地聚集的北约领导人正表达哀悼
...where gathering NATO leaders are offering their condolences

00:32:51.540 --> 00:32:53.700
与坚定支持
and unyielding solidarity.

00:32:53.700 --> 00:32:57.040
这场本该是北大西洋联盟的庆典
What was meant to be a celebration of the North Atlantic Alliance

00:32:57.040 --> 00:33:00.580
此刻被前所未有的震惊与哀悼淹没
is now a time of unprecedented shock and mourning.

00:33:14.330 --> 00:33:15.290
妈呀
Oh, geez.

00:33:19.620 --> 00:33:20.540
你还好吗
You okay?

00:33:21.080 --> 00:33:22.950
还好 你呢
Yeah. You?

00:33:24.160 --> 00:33:26.120
他们怎么上我的飞机的
How the hell'd they get on my plane?

00:33:26.120 --> 00:33:28.540
肯定是有内奸帮忙
With the help of someone on the inside, that's for sure.

00:33:31.370 --> 00:33:33.910
波兰边境要往那边走24公里
The Polish border is about 15 miles that way.

00:33:33.910 --> 00:33:36.580
步行的话我们明早就能到安全屋了
On foot, we can be at that safe house by morning.

00:33:36.580 --> 00:33:38.660
不用 救援马上就到
No. The cavalry's coming.

00:33:39.250 --> 00:33:40.660
不会有救援的 伙计
Cavalry's not coming, mate.

00:33:40.660 --> 00:33:43.040
白俄罗斯会控制坠机现场
Belarus will want to control the crash site.

00:33:43.540 --> 00:33:45.790
他们不会让任何飞机进入领空的
Won't be letting any planes into their airspace,

00:33:45.790 --> 00:33:50.490
我们的人不可能为了捡尸体 偷偷穿越敌军防线
and there's no way our guys are sneaking across enemy lines to retrieve corpses.

00:33:50.500 --> 00:33:53.290
他们只能当无人生还
They have to assume there are no survivors.

00:33:54.370 --> 00:33:55.410
该死
Shit.

00:33:56.410 --> 00:33:57.870
你在干什么
What are you doing?

00:33:57.870 --> 00:34:00.040
给我妻子打电话 我要让她知道我还活着
Calling my wife. I'm letting her know I'm alive.

00:34:00.040 --> 00:34:02.290
不行 不能打电话 好吗
No. No, no, no, no. No. No phones. All right?

00:34:02.290 --> 00:34:03.910
- 照我说的做 - 什么
Do as I do.

00:34:03.910 --> 00:34:07.040
我们刚经历了史上最严重的安全漏洞
We just survived the worst security breach in history,

00:34:07.040 --> 00:34:09.330
