你想做个交易吗
Maybe we could make a deal?

00:46:52.080 --> 00:46:52.910
什么交易
What?

00:47:05.200 --> 00:47:07.330
我想好回忆录怎么写了
Think I'm ready to write those memoirs now.

00:47:32.870 --> 00:47:33.830
谢谢
Thank you.

00:47:35.200 --> 00:47:36.040
给你
Take this.

00:47:38.040 --> 00:47:39.500
我很荣幸
It was my pleasure...

00:47:40.370 --> 00:47:41.910
总统先生
Mr. President.

00:47:44.250 --> 00:47:46.080
祝你们好运
Good luck to both of you.

00:48:09.700 --> 00:48:15.290
先生 “梯队”截获了华沙中情局 安全屋的监控录像
Sir, Echelon intercepted security footage from a CIA safe house in Warsaw

00:48:15.290 --> 00:48:18.040
有两个人刚刚进去了
that just buzzed in two guests.

00:48:19.830 --> 00:48:21.080
恕我直言
With all due respect,

00:48:21.080 --> 00:48:23.370
我们击落空军一号时 已经拿到了需要的东西
we got what we needed when we took down Air Force One.

00:48:23.540 --> 00:48:25.200
闭嘴
Quiet your mouth.

00:48:25.750 --> 00:48:29.660
我们的行动很隐蔽 就算他们活着又能怎么样
And we kept our footprint tight, so who cares if they live?

00:48:29.660 --> 00:48:32.000
我说要他们死 他们就得死
They die because I say they die.

00:48:38.370 --> 00:48:40.370
他们还活着 在华沙
They're alive. Warsaw.

00:48:41.620 --> 00:48:43.120
华沙 出发
Warsaw! Let's go!

00:48:58.910 --> 00:48:59.750
你还活着
You're alive.

00:49:03.410 --> 00:49:06.370
嘿 你因为我哭了
Okay. Hey. Are you crying because of me?

00:49:06.370 --> 00:49:07.990
是啊 当然 伙计
Hell yeah, I am, man.

00:49:08.000 --> 00:49:09.290
我是说 先生
I mean, sir.

00:49:10.500 --> 00:49:12.200
对不起 我是马蒂科米尔
I'm sorry. Marty Comer.

00:49:12.200 --> 00:49:13.330
好吧...
Oh, well.

00:49:14.450 --> 00:49:16.660
基站探员 超级粉丝
Station agent. A huge fan.

00:49:17.410 --> 00:49:18.540
还是个爱国者
Patriot.

00:49:18.750 --> 00:49:21.700
我是英国首相萨姆克拉克 我们能进去吗
Sam Clarke, British prime minister. Can we come in?

00:49:21.700 --> 00:49:22.750
可以
Yeah.

00:49:23.540 --> 00:49:25.160
当然可以
Yeah, of course, of course.

00:49:25.160 --> 00:49:26.120
那我们进去了
Like, now?

00:49:26.120 --> 00:49:27.450
- 好的 请进 - 谢谢
- Yeah, now. - Thank you.

00:49:27.450 --> 00:49:28.620
这边
Right this way.

00:49:28.620 --> 00:49:31.910
好吧 我知道这听起来很疯狂
Okay, so I know this sounds, uh, bonkers,

00:49:32.250 --> 00:49:34.080
- 但... - 有预案吗
- but... - What's the playbook on this?

00:49:34.080 --> 00:49:35.160
这事的预案
For this?

00:49:35.910 --> 00:49:38.620
哪有这种预案啊 我是说
Th-There is no damn playbook.

00:49:38.620 --> 00:49:41.870
我们预案多得很 有针对极移的预案
I mean-- And we got lots of playbooks. Ones that account for pole shifts,

00:49:41.870 --> 00:49:44.330
针对电脑有自我意识 太空猴子袭击
computers becoming self-aware, space monkey attacks,

00:49:44.330 --> 00:49:46.160
各种乱七八糟的预案
all kinds of hectic shit.

00:49:46.160 --> 00:49:50.160
但就是没有全世界目睹你们死亡
But, uh, none that contemplate you two sauntering in here

00:49:50.160 --> 00:49:52.700
然后又大摇大摆出现的预案
after dying in front of the entire planet's eyes.

00:49:52.700 --> 00:49:53.830
所以没有预案
So no playbook?

00:49:54.450 --> 00:49:55.700
现做一个吧
Let's make one.

00:49:56.700 --> 00:49:59.580
世人总说“英雄注定令人失望” 但请容我反驳
They say never meet your heroes, but to them I say:

00:49:59.580 --> 00:50:02.500
他们显然从未见识过 威廉姆马修德林杰总统的非凡魅力
You've never met President William Matthew Derringer.

00:50:03.080 --> 00:50:05.080
你名字首字母缩写 意思是大规模杀伤性武器
Your initials are WMD?

00:50:05.080 --> 00:50:06.660
是啊 很讨厌 对吧
Yeah. Pretty bitchin', right?

00:50:10.250 --> 00:50:11.660
跟我来 先生们
Follow me, gentlemen.

00:50:11.660 --> 00:50:13.370
顺便说一句 你们来得正好
Your timing's great, by the way.

00:50:13.370 --> 00:50:16.450
大使刚刚紧急把 所有在境人员召回了使馆
The ambassador just recalled all in-country personnel to the embassy.

00:50:16.450 --> 00:50:19.200
外面的世界情况很糟糕
It's a real nut punch in a Ziploc bag out there.

00:50:19.200 --> 00:50:22.040
要我说这些也不是巧合
And it ain't exactly a coincidence, if you ask me.

00:50:22.540 --> 00:50:23.580
等等 什么不是巧合
W-Wait, what's not?

00:50:23.580 --> 00:50:25.120
首先是你俩坠机
Well, first you two go down,

00:50:25.120 --> 00:50:28.290
然后在北约会议现场 有人突然投下一枚“政治手雷”
and then someone rolls a political grenade into that NATO conference.

00:50:31.000 --> 00:50:32.830
你们没听说吗
You guys didn't hear?

00:50:33.410 --> 00:50:35.290
没有 我们今天有点忙
No, we've had a pretty busy day.

00:50:36.750 --> 00:50:41.370
显然 “梯队”服务器被渗透了
Well, apparently, Echelon servers were infiltrated.

00:50:44.830 --> 00:50:48.870
两小时前 一批机密文件被泄露
Two hours ago, a tranche of classified documents were leaked,

00:50:48.870 --> 00:50:52.660
揭露了北约成员国数十年的秘密行动
exposing decades of covert activity amongst NATO members:

00:50:52.660 --> 00:50:58.290
工业间谍 经济破坏 干预外国选举
industrial espionage, economic sabotage and the influencing of foreign elections.

00:50:58.290 --> 00:51:01.620
最令人愤慨的是 这些行径并非针对敌对国家
And the real pisser? These weren't acts committed against enemy nations

00:51:01.620 --> 00:51:04.620
而是针对彼此 是盟友间的相互倾轧
but against each other. These were friends against friends.

00:51:04.620 --> 00:51:08.120
这简直是《老友记》第二季里 莫妮卡和瑞秋那种级别的塑料姐妹情
I'm talking some real Monica and Rachel season two shit.

00:51:08.580 --> 00:51:12.370
明天的峰会将会是 电话亭中的困兽之斗
I mean, tomorrow's summit's gonna be a monkey knife fight in a telephone booth.

00:51:13.290 --> 00:51:15.370
德国刚发现法国安插记者
Germany just found out France embedded journalists

00:51:15.370 --> 00:51:16.950
干预其大选
to influence their last election.

00:51:16.950 --> 00:51:19.370
捷克要求将意大利逐出北约
The Czech Republic wants Italy kicked out of the building

00:51:19.370 --> 00:51:21.120
因为意大利蓄意破坏他们的经济
for trying to tank their economy.

00:51:21.120 --> 00:51:25.540
而此刻我们却被挡在 全球最强的监控系统门外
All while we're locked out of the most powerful surveillance tool on this planet.

00:51:25.540 --> 00:51:27.450
泄露了多少档案
How many files are we talking about?

00:51:27.450 --> 00:51:29.240
两万 数量还在增加
20,000 and counting.

00:51:29.250 --> 00:51:31.910
这是史上最具破坏性的国家机密泄露
It's the most damaging leak of state secrets in history.

00:51:31.910 --> 00:51:35.450
有人在利用“梯队” 破坏北约组织的结构
Someone is using Echelon to tear at the very fabric of NATO.

00:51:35.450 --> 00:51:38.500
北约一直在破坏自己的组织结构
Sounds like NATO has been tearing at the fabric of itself.

00:51:39.120 --> 00:51:41.330
我打赌你很想说:“我早这么说过了”
Bet you're dying to say "I told you so."

00:51:41.330 --> 00:51:45.120
- 你说什么  - 你当初是喊着“美国优先”赢的初选
- Excuse me? - You ran your primaries on "America first."

00:51:46.370 --> 00:51:50.410
西蒙 我允许你来这里 是出于对威廉的尊重
Simone, I am allowing you to be in this room out of respect for Will.

00:51:50.410 --> 00:51:51.490
允许我
Allowing me?

00:51:51.500 --> 00:51:55.950
但请不要暗示 我对这个联盟有所保留
But please don't ever insinuate that I'm not all in on this alliance.

00:51:56.540 --> 00:52:00.740
如果北约垮台 就再无针对专制独裁者的屏障了
If NATO falls, there's no more backstop against despots and dictators.

00:52:00.750 --> 00:52:02.160
他们将不受任何制约
They run unchecked.

00:52:02.160 --> 00:52:03.990
这可能会引发一系列事件
It could set off a series of events that-that would

00:52:04.000 --> 00:52:06.830
破坏欧洲和世界其他地区的稳定
destabilize Europe and the rest of the world.

00:52:06.830 --> 00:52:10.790
我们正在讨论的是 全球范围内冲突升级 秩序崩坏
We are talking about the potential for increased conflict, chaos

00:52:10.790 --> 00:52:15.330
乃至真实战争威胁的可能性
and the very real threat of war on a global scale.

00:52:17.540 --> 00:52:18.990
我们得出面证明自己还活着
We put our heads above water.

00:52:19.000 --> 00:52:20.950
打给大使馆 通知他们我们在这里
Call the embassy. Let them know you have us.

00:52:20.950 --> 00:52:24.120
不行 我们得假设 所有高官都已被渗透
No, we have to assume all high command posts are compromised.

00:52:24.120 --> 00:52:25.250
胡说
Bullshit.

00:52:25.790 --> 00:52:27.990
我们在一个安全的美国设施里
We are in a secure U.S. facility.

00:52:28.000 --> 00:52:29.540
想尝尝品客薯片不
You guys want a hit of these Pringles?

00:52:29.540 --> 00:52:33.000
上次我在安全的美国设施里时 我们被从四万英尺高空击落
Last time I was in one of those, we got shot out of the sky at 40,000 feet.

00:52:34.620 --> 00:52:35.580
打电话
Make the call.

00:52:36.290 --> 00:52:37.290
不许打电话
Don't make the call.

00:52:37.290 --> 00:52:39.000
打电话
Make the call.

00:52:40.120 --> 00:52:41.370
不许打电话
Don't make the call.

00:52:42.370 --> 00:52:43.620
这电话我打不了
I can't make the call.

00:52:43.620 --> 00:52:45.490
我是总司令 打电话
I'm the commander in chief! Make the goddamn call.

00:52:45.500 --> 00:52:46.580
线路断了
The line's dead.

00:52:48.160 --> 00:52:49.250
这正常吗
Is that normal?

00:52:50.040 --> 00:52:50.910
不正常
No.

00:53:03.540 --> 00:53:05.080
有些人是真想让我们死啊
Somebody really wants us dead.

00:53:05.080 --> 00:53:06.750
我们在安全屋里很安全 对吧
We're safe, we're in a safe house, right?

00:53:09.580 --> 00:53:10.620
我们能搞定的
We got this.

00:53:12.950 --> 00:53:14.540
这些能给你们安全感吗
That feel safe enough for you?

00:53:29.330 --> 00:53:31.580
- 该死 - 这可不是演电影 小伙子
- Shit. - Not in the movies now, son.

00:53:50.250 --> 00:53:51.240
好了 听好
Okay, listen up.

00:53:51.250 --> 00:53:54.200
我会带你们离开 但万一情况不妙
I'm gonna get you guys out of here, but just in case things do go south,

00:53:54.200 --> 00:53:56.120
从第二出口撤退
best to beat a retreat through the secondary exit.

00:53:56.120 --> 00:53:59.160
从这里出去左转 穿过大厅再左转 有个宿舍房间
That's a left out of here, down the hall, make a left. That's the bunk room.

00:53:59.160 --> 00:54:01.120
右手边墙上有张海报
Another right, you should see a poster on the wall.

00:54:01.120 --> 00:54:04.450
冲着海报打一拳就能顺利撤离了
You punch through that poster, you should be good to go.

00:54:13.540 --> 00:54:14.700
帮我把电缆拉好 伙计们
Feed me, boys.

00:55:02.450 --> 00:55:04.790
萨沙 萨沙

00:55:05.080 --> 00:55:06.830
全都给我进来 快
All of you in here! Now!

00:55:24.120 --> 00:55:25.740
这小子真疯啊
That boy's a nutter.

00:55:25.750 --> 00:55:26.870
也许吧
Maybe,

00:55:26.870 --> 00:55:28.450
我们大美国的疯子
but he's America's nutter.

00:56:09.160 --> 00:56:10.160
走
Let's move.

00:56:40.330 --> 00:56:41.160
快走
Get out of here.

00:56:46.040 --> 00:56:47.080
快走
Go!

00:57:00.080 --> 00:57:01.000
快走
Come on!

00:57:01.580 --> 00:57:03.330
不对 这边 他说右转
No, no, this way. He said right!

00:57:05.250 --> 00:57:06.080
该死
Damn it!

00:57:10.540 --> 00:57:12.120
别修了 约翰兰博 快走
No, no, Rambo! Come on!

00:57:15.950 --> 00:57:17.120
找到海报了
Oh, found the poster.

00:57:17.790 --> 00:57:18.620
打一拳
Punch it.

00:57:19.080 --> 00:57:20.290
该死
Oh, goddamn it.

00:57:20.290 --> 00:57:21.950
- 有什么问题  - 我做不到
- What's the problem? - I can't.

00:57:25.700 --> 00:57:27.910
你是在搞笑吗 赶紧的啊
You having a laugh?! Come on!

00:57:27.910 --> 00:57:29.000
原谅我
Forgive me.

00:57:53.500 --> 00:57:54.830
我觉得我好像把那家伙干掉了
I think I killed that guy.

00:57:55.200 --> 00:57:56.870
你干掉的只有那面墙
Only thing you killed is the wall.

00:57:57.790 --> 00:57:59.120
不过我不得不说
I have to say, though,

00:57:59.120 --> 00:58:01.450
你拿枪的样子确实挺酷
you do look good with a gun in your hand.

00:58:05.040 --> 00:58:06.580
- 你先出去 - 不 你先出去
- You should go. - No, you go.

00:58:11.910 --> 00:58:13.040
放下枪
Drop your guns!

00:58:15.750 --> 00:58:16.700
抓到他们了
We have them.

00:58:17.950 --> 00:58:19.000
收到
Coming down.

00:58:48.250 --> 00:58:49.120
诺埃尔
Noel?

00:58:50.250 --> 00:58:51.200
萨姆
Sam?

00:58:53.620 --> 00:58:56.370
我以为你死了
- I thought you were dead. - I thought you were dead.

00:58:57.160 --> 00:58:58.410
你怎么会没死呢
How are you not dead?

00:58:59.000 --> 00:59:00.830
你们俩认识
You two know each other?

00:59:00.830 --> 00:59:03.660
- 我们... - 我们以前是同事
- We... - We worked together. Back in the day.

00:59:06.160 --> 00:59:07.200
你怎么找到我们的
How'd you find us?

00:59:15.750 --> 00:59:16.620
不要

00:59:19.250 --> 00:59:20.580
好吧 我告诉你
All right, I'll tell you!

00:59:33.540 --> 00:59:34.620
说来话长
Long story.

00:59:35.250 --> 00:59:36.540
嘿 你的后援呢
Hey, where's your backup?

00:59:36.540 --> 00:59:38.080
没有后援
There is no backup.

00:59:53.080 --> 00:59:54.990
我从西班牙就开始跟踪格拉多夫了
I've been trailing Gradov since Spain.

00:59:55.000 --> 00:59:57.240
- 维克托格拉多夫是幕后黑手  - 那个军火贩子
- Victor Gradov is behind this? - The gun guy?

00:59:57.250 --> 01:00:00.370
你是说 这一切都是 为了报复我们阻止他制造核武器
So you're saying this is all payback because we stopped him building nukes?

01:00:00.370 --> 01:00:01.290
那边走
That way.

01:00:01.290 --> 01:00:03.040
格拉多夫没有造核弹
Gradov wasn't building a nuke.

01:00:03.040 --> 01:00:04.870
但他是个军火商啊
But he was a weapons developer.

01:00:04.870 --> 01:00:06.620
他是 但他的儿子不是
He was, but his son wasn't.

01:00:06.620 --> 01:00:09.450
- 他儿子跟这有什么关系  - 他儿子是个科学家
- Yeah, what's his son got to do with it? - His son was a scientist.

01:00:09.450 --> 01:00:12.040
他非常聪明 取得了令人难以置信的突破
He was brilliant and made incredible breakthroughs.

01:00:12.450 --> 01:00:13.830
他本来马上就能造出
He was on the brink of onlining

01:00:13.830 --> 01:00:17.040
全球第一个“免堆芯融毁”核反应堆
the first ever nuclear reactor incapable of melting down.

01:00:17.830 --> 01:00:19.330
球床反应堆技术
The pebble-bed technology.

01:00:19.750 --> 01:00:21.450
我们那个球床反应堆技术
Our pebble-bed technology?

01:00:21.450 --> 01:00:23.540
我们告诉全世界是我们研发的那个
The same technology I just told the world that we developed?

01:00:23.540 --> 01:00:25.080
其实是格拉多夫的儿子发明的
You're telling me Gradov's son invented it?

01:00:25.080 --> 01:00:26.330
他差一点就成功了
He was close.

01:00:26.330 --> 01:00:28.200
当时他还需要一些浓缩钚
He still needed the enriched plutonium,

01:00:28.200 --> 01:00:30.290
他父亲从黑市给他买了一批
which his father procured from the black market.

01:00:30.290 --> 01:00:31.990
这笔交易被“梯队”监测到了
Echelon picked up on that transaction.

01:00:32.000 --> 01:00:34.540
理所当然 我们以为他们要造核武器
Of course we assumed it was to build a weapon.

01:00:35.040 --> 01:00:38.200
所以我们做了面对核威胁时该做的事
So we did what one does when faced with a nuclear threat.

01:00:38.200 --> 01:00:40.200
我们朝额头扔弹头了
You dropped warheads on foreheads?

01:00:40.200 --> 01:00:41.120
没错
We did.

01:00:41.750 --> 01:00:43.620
死者中就有格拉多夫的儿子
Gradov's son was amongst the dead.

01:00:44.910 --> 01:00:46.790
那次行动是北约批准的
The operation was sanctioned by NATO.

01:00:47.830 --> 01:00:50.330
我们承担不起他制造核弹的风险
We couldn't risk the chance that he was building a nuke.

01:00:50.830 --> 01:00:52.620
那会危机数百万人的生命
Millions of lives were at stake.

01:00:53.160 --> 01:00:56.290
事后我们才发现他造的到底是什么
It was only in the aftermath we realized what was actually being developed.

01:00:56.910 --> 01:01:00.540
于是在“梯队”的帮助下 我们得到了球床反应堆技术的图纸
So with the help of Echelon, we procured the schematics for the pebble-bed tech.

01:01:00.540 --> 01:01:01.450
躲起来
Get back.

01:01:09.370 --> 01:01:11.410
所以我们夺走了 他儿子的性命和遗产
So we took his son's life and then his legacy, huh?

01:01:11.410 --> 01:01:13.990
还打算为此在得里雅斯特大肆庆祝
Which we were about to take a big victory lap for in Trieste.

01:01:14.000 --> 01:01:16.370
恕我直言 但好像我们才是反派啊
Correct me if I'm doing the math wrong, but we're the assholes here.

01:01:16.370 --> 01:01:19.870
听着 格拉多夫的儿子 不是因我们而死
Okay, look. Gradov's son didn't die because of us.

01:01:19.870 --> 01:01:22.080
他死是因为他是魔鬼的儿子
He died because he's the son of the devil.

01:01:22.950 --> 01:01:24.040
继续走
Let's keep it moving.

01:01:25.660 --> 01:01:28.540
没有最高级别安全 格拉多夫是不可能做到的
Gradov couldn't have done all this without top-level security clearance.

01:01:28.540 --> 01:01:31.790
问题是格拉多夫的内奸到底是谁
Okay, so then the question is: Who was Gradov working with on the inside?

01:01:31.790 --> 01:01:34.040
得从那个安排我们登机的人开始查起
Got to start with the guy who put us both in that plane.

01:01:34.950 --> 01:01:35.790
什么
What?

01:01:36.000 --> 01:01:37.540
你本不该和我一起飞的
You weren't supposed to fly with me.

01:01:38.040 --> 01:01:40.370
有人刻意向你灌输这个念头 并持续强化它
Somebody put that idea in your head, insisted on it.

01:01:42.200 --> 01:01:43.250
昆西
Quincy.

01:01:48.580 --> 01:01:50.410
华沙一处安全屋遭到袭击
A safe house was hit in Warsaw.

01:01:51.290 --> 01:01:52.200
你觉得是怎么回事
What are you thinking?

01:01:52.870 --> 01:01:54.240
可能是威廉和萨姆吗
Could be Will and Sam?

01:01:54.250 --> 01:01:56.790
一定有什么值得追查的
There must have been something in there worth going after.

01:01:57.450 --> 01:02:00.370
- 我们必须考虑这种可能性... - 难道你看到的和我们不一样
- We have to consider the possibility... - Did you not see what we all saw?

01:02:00.370 --> 01:02:02.790
他们和空军一号一起坠毁了
They went down with Air Force One.

01:02:02.790 --> 01:02:05.620
我不会放弃希望的 至少目前不会
I'm not giving up hope. Not yet.

01:02:05.620 --> 01:02:07.040
我们都不该放弃
None of us should be.

01:02:07.040 --> 01:02:10.040
我们必须集中精力 处理这次“梯队”泄密事件
We need to focus all our energies on this Echelon leak.

01:02:10.040 --> 01:02:11.540
舆论愈演愈烈
The rhetoric is heating up.

01:02:11.540 --> 01:02:14.580
但如果威廉和萨姆可能还活着...
But if there's even a chance that Will and Sam are still alive...

01:02:14.580 --> 01:02:17.870
我们让中情局负责调查华沙的安全屋 而在这栋大楼里
We put CIA on the safe house in Warsaw. And right here in this building,

01:02:17.870 --> 01:02:20.080
重点是和北约一起控制事态恶化
the focus is on stopping the bleeding with NATO.

01:02:20.080 --> 01:02:23.830
我想尽快与 意大利 德国和法国会面
I want an audience with Italy, Germany and France as soon as possible.

01:02:23.830 --> 01:02:25.990
让这些家伙们别再惺惺作态
It's time these guys stopped clutching their pearls

01:02:26.000 --> 01:02:28.080
赶紧开始履行领导职责
and get on with the business of leading.

01:02:29.080 --> 01:02:30.620
是我儿子 见谅
It's my son. Excuse me.

01:02:31.410 --> 01:02:32.290
嗨 亲爱的
Hi, sweetheart.

01:02:32.290 --> 01:02:35.450
西蒙 我知道威廉对你有多重要
Simone, I appreciate how much Will meant to you.

01:02:35.450 --> 01:02:38.000
我知道他像你亲兄弟一样 但他已经死了
I know he was like a brother, but he's gone.

01:02:38.450 --> 01:02:39.910
他们都死了
They're both gone.

01:02:40.500 --> 01:02:42.910
你得开始接受这个现实
You need to start wrapping your head around that.

01:02:47.250 --> 01:02:48.830
不可能是昆西
There's no way it's Quincy.

01:02:49.000 --> 01:02:49.990
你怎么能确定
How can you be sure?

01:02:50.000 --> 01:02:52.830
他是我的幕僚长 大学时代就相识的老搭档
He's been my chief of staff for six years. I known him since university.

01:02:52.830 --> 01:02:55.410
是普通人眼里的他 还是你认知中的他
The way normal people know him or the way you know people?

01:02:55.410 --> 01:02:56.790
又开始了
Ah, don't start that shit again.

01:02:56.790 --> 01:02:59.040
他喜欢香肠薯泥还是炸鱼薯条
Does he like bangers and mash or fish and chips?

01:02:59.040 --> 01:03:00.330
我知道你想干嘛
Ah, I see what you did there.

01:03:00.330 --> 01:03:02.950
又想开始讨论炸鱼薯条的事
Sneaking the fish and chips back into the conversation.

01:03:02.950 --> 01:03:05.410
为了这事你可真是绞尽脑汁啊
You must be exhausted trying to figure that out.

01:03:05.410 --> 01:03:07.870
别互相挑来挑去 我们需要保持统一口味
Stop chipping away at each other. We need to be on the same page.

01:03:07.870 --> 01:03:10.410
- 她是在用双关讽刺我们  - 她喜欢双关
- Did she just hit us with a pun? - She loves a pun.

01:03:10.410 --> 01:03:12.870
我告诉过她 双关只适合心思简单的人
I tried to tell her puns are for simple people.

01:03:12.870 --> 01:03:13.870
可我喜欢双关啊
I love puns.

01:03:13.870 --> 01:03:15.620
- 说的就是你 - 各位
- My point exactly. - Guys!

01:03:17.450 --> 01:03:18.370
这边
Over here.

01:03:19.250 --> 01:03:20.200
快过来
Come on.

01:03:21.120 --> 01:03:23.450
听着 现在关键是去得里雅斯特
Look, right now the key is getting to Trieste.

01:03:23.450 --> 01:03:24.370
得里雅斯特
Trieste?

01:03:24.370 --> 01:03:26.870
美国大使馆离这里有多远  他们能帮忙
How far away is the U.S. embassy from here? They can help us.

01:03:26.870 --> 01:03:28.540
我们不去大使馆
We're not going to the embassy.

01:03:29.700 --> 01:03:31.700
等等 你们怎么都不让我去大使馆
Wait, why won't anyone let me go to my embassy?

01:03:31.700 --> 01:03:34.040
为什么大家突然都反对大使馆了
What does everybody suddenly have against embassies?

01:03:35.540 --> 01:03:38.950
我们得假定所有高官都已被渗透
We have to presume that all high command posts are compromised.

01:03:38.950 --> 01:03:40.540
你再说一遍我会尖叫的
Say that again, I'm gonna scream.

01:03:40.540 --> 01:03:42.750
不是普通尖叫 而是喉底迸发的哀嚎
Not just a conventional scream, a guttural wail.

01:03:43.910 --> 01:03:44.750
我们走
Let's go.

01:03:45.540 --> 01:03:47.660
听着 我才是总司令
Listen, I'm the commander in chief.

01:03:47.660 --> 01:03:49.990
好吧 恕我直言先生 你不是
Okay, respectfully, sir, no, you're not.

01:03:50.000 --> 01:03:52.450
副总统几小时前已宣誓就职
The vice president was sworn in a few hours ago.

01:03:53.000 --> 01:03:55.790
至于他 他从来都不是总司令
And he has never been commander in chief of anything.

01:03:55.790 --> 01:03:56.700
国王才是
The king is.

01:03:56.700 --> 01:04:00.540
事实上他是唯一一个 不是真正国家元首的国家元首
In fact, he's the only head of state that's not an actual head of state.

01:04:00.540 --> 01:04:02.080
国王才是
Again, king.

01:04:02.080 --> 01:04:04.540
你们只是两个倒霉蛋
You're just two guys that are shit out of luck.

01:04:04.540 --> 01:04:05.500
所以 走吧
So let's go.

01:04:06.450 --> 01:04:07.290
来吧
Come on.

01:04:14.620 --> 01:04:16.910
你们现在是我的包裹
You are now my package.

01:04:16.910 --> 01:04:18.040
也是我的任务
My mission.

01:04:18.040 --> 01:04:20.040
我的任务就是把你俩活着
And my mission is to deliver you alive

01:04:20.040 --> 01:04:21.990
送到这片大陆上最安全的地方去
to the most secure location on this continent,

01:04:22.000 --> 01:04:24.290
也就是在得里雅斯特的北约峰会
and that is the NATO summit in Trieste.

01:04:24.910 --> 01:04:29.200
要让任务不脱轨 这列火车就是我们最好的机会
And my best shot at keeping this mission on track is that train.

01:04:31.450 --> 01:04:33.540
双关 这次不是故意的
Pun, this time, not intended!

01:04:34.120 --> 01:04:36.330
你是带我们开火车的车头吗
You seem very "locomotivated"!

01:04:36.830 --> 01:04:39.910
只是想确保计划不会脱轨
Trying to make sure this thing doesn't go off the rails!

01:04:40.330 --> 01:04:41.740
果然如此
Ha! Well, that confirms it!

01:04:41.750 --> 01:04:44.000
坠机时我肯定已经死了 跟你俩在一起简直是地狱
I died in that plane crash, and this is hell!

01:04:50.200 --> 01:04:51.080
加油
Come on!

01:04:52.540 --> 01:04:53.500
拉住你了

01:04:55.660 --> 01:04:56.620
你还好吗
You good?

01:04:56.620 --> 01:04:57.660
谢谢
Thank you.

01:06:02.250 --> 01:06:04.500
你的团队在西班牙的事...
About your team in Spain.

01:06:07.500 --> 01:06:08.660
我们都失去了很多
We've all lost a lot.

01:06:10.910 --> 01:06:12.910
听着 我欠你...
Look, I-I owe you a...

01:06:12.910 --> 01:06:14.910
请你不要说抱歉
Please don't say an apology.

01:06:14.910 --> 01:06:18.040
只是想解释下 的黎波里之后我为什么消失了
An explanation for disappearing after Tripoli.

01:06:20.040 --> 01:06:21.370
在的黎波里发生了什么
What happened in Tripoli?

01:06:23.290 --> 01:06:24.620
不关你的事
None of your business.

01:06:24.620 --> 01:06:26.370
继续睡觉吧
Go back to sleep.

01:06:26.370 --> 01:06:28.700
首先 你没有在的黎波里消失
Okay, first of all, you didn't disappear in Tripoli.

01:06:28.700 --> 01:06:30.830
你无处不在
You appeared everywhere.

01:06:31.080 --> 01:06:32.830
你上过电视 报纸 社交媒体...
You were on TV, newspapers, social media...

01:06:32.830 --> 01:06:35.830
- 我在竞选公职 - 你在逃避
- I was running for office. - You were running away.

01:06:35.830 --> 01:06:36.950
是因为爱吗
Was it love?

01:06:38.080 --> 01:06:40.330
你在逃避爱吗
Were you running away from love?

01:06:40.330 --> 01:06:42.490
你能管好自己的事吗
Can you stay in your lane?

01:06:42.500 --> 01:06:44.620
你本可以跟我一起
And you could have come with me.

01:06:45.500 --> 01:06:46.870
一起参加竞选活动
On the campaign trail?

01:06:46.870 --> 01:06:51.200
比如去上早间节目 和全世界分享我妈妈的千层面食谱
Like, go on breakfast TV and share my mom's lasagna recipe with the world?

01:06:51.200 --> 01:06:52.790
我们本可以在一起的
We would have been together.

01:06:53.660 --> 01:06:55.000
不 萨姆
No, Sam.

01:06:56.370 --> 01:06:58.000
我们不可能在一起的
We couldn't have been together.

01:07:02.330 --> 01:07:05.240
我去吃点东西 需要什么吗 总统先生
I'm gonna go get something to eat. Can I get you anything, Mr. President?

01:07:05.250 --> 01:07:07.450
你吃什么给我带一份就行
I'll have whatever you're having.

01:07:07.700 --> 01:07:08.950
没问题
You got it.

01:07:19.580 --> 01:07:21.620
我可能要问越界的问题了
I'm just gonna go out on a limb here.

01:07:21.620 --> 01:07:24.500
你们俩以前不只是同事关系对吧
You two did a little more than work together back in the day, huh?

01:07:25.750 --> 01:07:27.290
我是说 她看起来人很好
I mean, she seems nice.

01:07:28.200 --> 01:07:30.580
比你的最好朋友幕僚长好多了
A lot better than that best friend chief of staff of yours

01:07:30.580 --> 01:07:34.200
- 那个卧底间谍 - 我不想和你聊这些
- that's a sleeper spy insurgent. - We're not having this conversation.

01:07:34.200 --> 01:07:37.120
听着 伙计 她在感情上有点淡漠
Listen, man, she's a little emotionally distant.

01:07:37.120 --> 01:07:38.750
不过很有幽默感
Great sense of humor, though.

01:07:39.660 --> 01:07:40.660
嘿
Hey.

01:07:41.040 --> 01:07:42.330
你们为什么分开了
Why'd you guys split up?

01:07:42.910 --> 01:07:45.240
又来了 不停问问题
And he's back. Back to questions.

01:07:45.250 --> 01:07:47.160
拜托 在的黎波里发生了什么
Come on. What happened in Tripoli?

01:07:47.160 --> 01:07:49.240
- 别问了 - 在的黎波里发生了什么 萨姆
- Don't. - Come on. What happened in Tripoli, Sam?

01:07:49.250 --> 01:07:50.990
别再说的黎波里了
Stop saying "Tripoli"!

01:07:51.000 --> 01:07:53.790
好吧 在利比亚首都发生了什么
Fine, what happened in the capital city of Libya?

01:07:54.950 --> 01:07:57.410
我在那里告诉了她我想竞选首相
It's where I told her that I wanted to run for office.

01:07:57.410 --> 01:07:58.490
你满意了吗
Are you happy now?

01:07:58.500 --> 01:08:00.910
- 你为什么想竞选  - 你还问
- And why'd you want to run for office? - Oh, God, are you still going?

01:08:00.910 --> 01:08:02.660
你为什么想竞选 萨姆
Why'd you want to run for office, Sam?

01:08:02.660 --> 01:08:06.700
因为我想为她打造一个更好的世界 我们可以一起在这世界里白头偕老
Because, because I wanted to build a better world for her and I to grow old in together!

01:08:11.580 --> 01:08:12.410
这真是...
That's...

01:08:15.370 --> 01:08:17.750
我听过的最浪漫的事
...the most romantic goddamn thing I've ever heard.

01:08:18.410 --> 01:08:19.540
她可不是...
Yeah, well, she didn't...

01:08:20.000 --> 01:08:21.540
她可不是这么想的
she didn't see it that way.

01:08:26.040 --> 01:08:27.950
- 该死  - 我们可以商量一下
- Shit! - Whoa, whoa. We can talk this out.

01:08:28.790 --> 01:08:31.450
我知道你们都很迷恋自己的声音
I know you're both enamored with the sound of your own voice,

01:08:31.450 --> 01:08:33.660
但你们谁也不许说话了
but there's no more talking.

01:08:37.700 --> 01:08:38.700
搞什么鬼
What the hell?!

01:08:51.120 --> 01:08:52.000
该死
Oh, shit.

01:08:52.750 --> 01:08:54.040
没想到会这样
Didn't see that coming.

01:08:56.750 --> 01:08:58.700
已经来不及了
Already short on time as it is.

01:08:59.540 --> 01:09:00.450
放下枪
Drop it.

01:09:01.660 --> 01:09:04.080
- 嘿 别开枪 - 我们得听他解释
- Whoa, hey. Don't shoot him. - We need to hear him out.

01:09:04.790 --> 01:09:06.790
你们想听他解释 边走边听吧
You want to hear him out? Let's do it on the move.

01:09:07.500 --> 01:09:08.330
走吧
Come on.

01:09:11.910 --> 01:09:15.990
我只想平静地度过余生 但格拉多夫找到了我
All I wanted to do was live my days out in peace, but Gradov found me,

01:09:16.000 --> 01:09:17.450
强行控制住我
put his claws into me,

01:09:17.450 --> 01:09:20.330
让我做我从来不想做的事
made me do things I never wanted to do.

01:09:20.870 --> 01:09:23.040
但现在发生的事
But what's happening now,

01:09:23.040 --> 01:09:26.500
我们正在做的事 已经太过了
what we've set into motion now, it's a bridge too far.

01:09:28.950 --> 01:09:30.990
我知道你们已经察觉
I know you've figured out there's an insider

01:09:31.000 --> 01:09:34.250
政府最高层有他的内奸 但是我...
working at the highest levels of government. And, no, I...

01:09:35.500 --> 01:09:36.620
我不知道...
I don't know...

01:09:37.290 --> 01:09:38.250
我不知道...
I don't know...

01:09:40.700 --> 01:09:42.330
我不知道是谁
I don't know who the insider is.

01:09:42.330 --> 01:09:46.290
我从没见过他们 但他们帮格拉多夫进入了“梯队”
I never saw them face-to-face. But they helped Gradov get into Echelon,

01:09:46.290 --> 01:09:48.660
帮他摧毁了空军一号
and they helped him take down Air Force One.

01:09:48.790 --> 01:09:50.740
我们怎么查出这个内奸是谁
Then how do we find out who this insider is?

01:09:50.750 --> 01:09:52.790
通过格拉多夫的安全通讯
Through Gradov's secure communications.

01:09:52.790 --> 01:09:55.290
我设计的通讯
Communications I designed.

01:09:55.290 --> 01:09:59.120
但你们必须马上下车
But you'll have to get off this train right now.

01:09:59.450 --> 01:10:00.620
车还在开呢
While it's moving?

01:10:00.620 --> 01:10:03.950
格拉多夫现在拥有上帝视角
Gradov's got the eyes of God at his disposal.

01:10:04.700 --> 01:10:08.080
他会派一队人在下一站等着杀了你们
They'll have a team waiting at the next station to kill you.

01:10:08.750 --> 01:10:09.660
- 真棒啊 - 真棒啊
- Great. - Great.

01:10:10.000 --> 01:10:13.120
听着 我在克罗地亚有个据点
Look, there's a building in Croatia

01:10:13.120 --> 01:10:16.160
那时我还不认识格拉多夫
I operated out of before I ever knew the name Gradov.

01:10:16.290 --> 01:10:20.200
去扎达尔的拉瓦斯卡街12号
Get to 12 Lavaska Street in Zadar.

01:10:20.200 --> 01:10:24.620
五楼有个加密终端站
There's a secure terminal there on the fifth floor.

01:10:24.620 --> 01:10:25.700
把手给我
Give me your hand.

01:10:28.250 --> 01:10:29.540
好了

01:10:29.660 --> 01:10:33.240
这个指令能运行我设计的一个程序
This prompt will run a program I designed

01:10:33.250 --> 01:10:40.120
定位所有涉密许可持有者 与其通讯轨迹
to trace communications he had with anyone carrying compartmented security clearance.

01:10:40.120 --> 01:10:41.500
运行这个程序
Run the program,

01:10:42.450 --> 01:10:44.080
你就能找到内奸
you'll find the insider.

01:10:46.120 --> 01:10:48.080
你们必须结束这一切
You have to end this.

01:10:48.660 --> 01:10:50.450
格拉多夫胃口太大
Gradov is insatiable.

01:10:51.250 --> 01:10:52.660
他永远不会停手的
He'll never stop.

01:10:56.410 --> 01:11:00.580
做点好事改变一下感觉真好
Feels nice to do something good for a change.

01:11:09.660 --> 01:11:11.000
该死 好吧
Shit. Okay.

01:11:11.700 --> 01:11:12.540
好吧
Okay.

01:11:13.410 --> 01:11:15.410
你知道吗 我们能搞定的 好吗
You know what? We got this, okay?

01:11:15.410 --> 01:11:17.700
《亡命跳跃》里 我可是从货运列车上跳下去的
Hell, I barrel-rolled off a freight train in Death Jumpers.

01:11:17.700 --> 01:11:19.120
你没跳 是你的替身跳的
No, you didn't. Your stuntman did.

01:11:19.120 --> 01:11:21.120
你非得这时候跟我抠字眼
Now? Now you want to bust me on a technicality?

01:11:21.120 --> 01:11:23.740
先生 恕我直言 没人能从这列火车上跳下去
Sir, respectfully, no one is barrel-rolling off of this train.

01:11:23.750 --> 01:11:26.700
是时候露头了 我们得打电话求助
I think it's time to raise your heads. We have to call someone.

01:11:26.700 --> 01:11:29.410
不行 我们得假定 所有高官都已被渗透
No, no, no. We have to assume that all high command posts are compromised.

01:11:29.410 --> 01:11:32.330
没错 如果我们现在露面 内奸就会开始演戏
Yes, and if we resurface now, the cover-up begins,

01:11:32.330 --> 01:11:35.290
我们永远无法知道内奸是谁 他们又能逍遥法外了
we never find out who's behind this, and they get to fight another day.

01:11:35.290 --> 01:11:37.790
所以你宁愿 跳下时速65公里的火车吗
So you'd rather jump off a train that's going 40 miles an hour?

01:11:37.790 --> 01:11:39.870
我们被动挨打已经太久了
We've been taking this on the chin for way too long,

01:11:39.870 --> 01:11:42.330
我受够了一直防守
and I'm done with being on the defensive!

01:11:43.370 --> 01:11:44.580
得了吧
Oh! Come on!

01:11:45.200 --> 01:11:46.660
好吧 嘿
All right, hey!

01:11:46.660 --> 01:11:48.830
记得把下巴缩到胸前
Just tuck your chin to your chest!

01:11:48.830 --> 01:11:51.160
- 你确定有用吗  - 相信我
- Sure that's gonna make a difference? - Trust me!

01:11:54.950 --> 01:11:56.040
我觉得他没事
I think he's okay.

01:11:56.790 --> 01:11:57.620
真是见鬼了
Damn you.

01:12:02.910 --> 01:12:04.200
雄起 德林杰
Man up, Derringer.

01:12:04.200 --> 01:12:05.990
你可是美国总统
You're the President of the United States.

01:12:06.000 --> 01:12:07.790
星条旗万岁
Stars and stripes forever!

01:12:07.790 --> 01:12:09.000
团身缓冲

01:12:13.450 --> 01:12:15.160
在中情局我们有个说法
At the CIA, we had a saying:

01:12:15.160 --> 01:12:18.410
“组织之力 源于个人
"The strength of the organization is the individual.

01:12:18.410 --> 01:12:21.910
“个人之力 成于组织”
The strength of the individual is the organization."

01:12:21.910 --> 01:12:25.830
在座的各位 正是这一精神的鲜活体现
The collective that sits in this room is the living embodiment of that.

01:12:26.370 --> 01:12:29.370
而某些人正企图操纵我们
And someone out there is manipulating us.

01:12:29.370 --> 01:12:31.200
分裂我们
Trying to tear us apart.

01:12:31.870 --> 01:12:34.740
所以让我们向幕后黑手传递一个信号
So let's send whoever's behind this a message.

01:12:34.750 --> 01:12:36.370
一致向外
Swing in the other direction.

01:12:36.370 --> 01:12:38.000
加倍投入北约
Double down on NATO.

01:12:38.160 --> 01:12:41.330
让他们明白 任何破坏这一联盟的企图
Let it be known that if you try and break this bond,

01:12:41.330 --> 01:12:43.700
只会让我们更强大
it will only make us stronger.

01:12:44.200 --> 01:12:45.410
这些感性的话挺可爱的
Those are lovely sentiments.

01:12:46.700 --> 01:12:49.410
但你说的这些得建立在信任之上
But what you're asking for is predicated on trust.

01:12:51.160 --> 01:12:53.500
我不信任这房间里的任何人
And I don't trust anyone in this room.

01:12:54.410 --> 01:12:56.330
- 总理 - 没关系
- Chancellor... - It's fine.

01:12:56.330 --> 01:12:57.330
让他走
Let him walk.

01:12:57.330 --> 01:12:59.540
现在是他的竞选季 他很害怕
He's in a campaign season. He's scared.

01:13:00.500 --> 01:13:02.910
猜猜下一届竞选我要主打什么
You know what I'm going to campaign on in the next cycle?

01:13:03.790 --> 01:13:05.870
退出这个联盟
Withdrawing from this alliance.

01:13:09.540 --> 01:13:10.500
没关系
It's okay.

01:13:11.080 --> 01:13:12.410
我们可以一起撑下去
We can hold this together.

01:13:12.410 --> 01:13:15.330
美国将承担他们的那部分费用
The U.S. will cover the cost of their contribution.

01:13:17.500 --> 01:13:19.410
这正是我们所需要的 不是吗
That's what we all need, isn't it?

01:13:19.870 --> 01:13:21.040
我想是的
I think so.

01:13:21.200 --> 01:13:24.000
美式傲慢又一次 被强塞进我们的喉咙
More American arrogance shoved down our throats.

01:13:25.620 --> 01:13:27.700
明天早上将进行投票
There will be a vote held in the morning

01:13:27.700 --> 01:13:32.330
25个国家已经同意解散北约 包括意大利
with 25 countries already on board to disband NATO, including Italy.

01:13:33.290 --> 01:13:35.000
到时见 总统女士
I'll see you there, Madam President.

01:13:40.160 --> 01:13:41.830
缩下巴还挺管用的吧
Man, the chin thing kind of worked, huh?

01:13:41.830 --> 01:13:43.990
好了 可别再提下巴了
All right, enough with the bloody chin thing.

01:13:44.000 --> 01:13:46.870
你下巴没事多亏了我的妙招好吧
You don't have a bloody chin thanks to my killer pro tip.

01:13:48.910 --> 01:13:50.620
干得好 兄弟 你惹她生气了
Way to go, bro. You made her mad.

01:14:08.700 --> 01:14:09.910
多谢
Thanks.

01:14:10.950 --> 01:14:13.790
天啊 哈蒙德选藏身地的品味真差啊
Geez, Hammond didn't have an incredibly sexy taste in hideouts, huh?

01:14:13.790 --> 01:14:16.200
有些人就喜欢躲在废弃的旧建筑里
Well, some people like to hide out in old derelict buildings,

01:14:16.200 --> 01:14:17.990
就像有些人喜欢吸羊奶头一样
and others like to suck on sheep nipples.

01:14:18.000 --> 01:14:20.540
- 谁吸羊奶头了  - 没谁
- Who sucks on sheep nipples? - Nobody sucks on sheep nipples!

01:14:23.160 --> 01:14:25.370
好吧 天啊 老天爷
Okay. God. Geez.

01:14:26.250 --> 01:14:28.080
- 几楼  - 五楼
- What floor? - Fifth.

01:14:28.080 --> 01:14:29.000
好吧
All right.

01:14:35.080 --> 01:14:36.410
快点 健身房强者
Come on, Gym Strong.

01:14:41.580 --> 01:14:42.910
这里什么都没有
There's nothing here.

01:14:42.910 --> 01:14:45.080
那个该死的王八蛋骗子
Hammond, that lying son of a bitch.

01:14:45.080 --> 01:14:46.620
把我们骗进了死胡同
Led us to a dead end.

01:14:47.950 --> 01:14:48.790
等等...
Unless...

01:14:52.410 --> 01:14:53.790
他没骗我们
...he didn't.

01:15:10.120 --> 01:15:11.080
太好了
Well, nice.

01:15:11.080 --> 01:15:12.330
好极了
Okay.

01:15:12.330 --> 01:15:13.450
你听到了吗
Do you hear that?

01:15:26.580 --> 01:15:28.370
感觉来者不善啊
That does not look like the cavalry!

01:15:31.330 --> 01:15:33.830
把自己锁在安全屋里 我来处理
Lock yourselves in the safe room. I'm gonna go handle this.

01:15:33.830 --> 01:15:37.200
只有你能从服务器上找到情报 我来拖住他们
No, no, no. You're the only one that can get the intel off the server. I'll hold them off.

01:15:37.200 --> 01:15:38.120
萨姆
Sam...

01:15:38.120 --> 01:15:40.450
- 你觉得我退步了吗  - 你确实退步了
- What, do you think I've lost a step? - I know you've lost a step.

01:15:40.450 --> 01:15:43.200
- 我只是不希望你死在我面前 - 快去吧
- I just don't want you dying on my watch. - Just go.

01:15:43.870 --> 01:15:44.870
我们能搞定的
We got this.

01:15:46.450 --> 01:15:48.620
你跟我来 我需要你的手
You're coming with me. I need your hand.

01:16:12.040 --> 01:16:13.500
我中枪了
I've been shot!

01:16:20.250 --> 01:16:21.080
你没事吧
You okay?

01:16:23.160 --> 01:16:24.160
没事
Yep!

01:16:26.830 --> 01:16:27.750
手
Hand.

01:16:32.040 --> 01:16:33.160
好了
Okay.

01:16:51.410 --> 01:16:52.410
不妙
Oh, shit.

01:17:05.120 --> 01:17:07.540
- 他没事吧  - 拖住他们了 但我们得走了
- Is he okay? - Yeah, he's holding them off, but we need to go.

01:17:35.700 --> 01:17:37.660
快点快点
Come on, come on, come on.

01:17:39.950 --> 01:17:41.160
好了 进去了
Okay, we're in.

01:17:42.750 --> 01:17:43.620
行动中止
Abort!

01:17:43.620 --> 01:17:45.040
撤退
Fall back!

01:17:47.500 --> 01:17:49.500
- 我找到内奸了 - 是的 是昆西
- I got the insider. - Yeah, it's Quincy.

01:17:52.000 --> 01:17:52.950
是布拉德肖
It's Bradshaw.

01:17:54.330 --> 01:17:55.250
胡说
Bullshit.

01:17:56.000 --> 01:17:57.490
证据呢 给我看看
Tell me where it says that.

01:17:57.500 --> 01:18:00.830
她和格拉多夫18个月前就开始联系了
There are dozens of communications between her and Gradov going back almost 18 months.

01:18:00.830 --> 01:18:03.200
这里全是她留下的电子痕迹
Her digital fingerprints are all over this.

01:18:03.750 --> 01:18:05.660
- 对不起 - 你不需要道歉
- I'm sorry. - You don't need to be sorry.

01:18:06.830 --> 01:18:09.330
等我抓到她 我会毁了她的世界
I'm gonna grind up her world when I get my hands on...

01:18:37.080 --> 01:18:38.080
卡住了
It's stuck.

01:19:11.000 --> 01:19:12.160
- 你还好吗  - 没事
- You okay?! - Yes!

01:19:12.160 --> 01:19:13.120
好的
Okay!

01:19:18.830 --> 01:19:19.700
萨姆
Sam.

01:19:32.080 --> 01:19:33.910
不

01:19:43.580 --> 01:19:45.160
我们得从这盒子里出去
We need to get out of this box.

01:19:45.580 --> 01:19:47.500
我需要你过来 快
I need you over here! Now!

01:19:49.950 --> 01:19:51.250
- 看到那个屋顶了吗  - 看到了
- You see that roof? - Yeah.

01:19:51.580 --> 01:19:53.290
尽量低一点 好吗
Get as low as you can, okay?

01:20:01.450 --> 01:20:02.370
准备好
Get ready.

01:20:05.290 --> 01:20:06.330
跳
Drop!

01:20:47.750 --> 01:20:48.830
已经处理好了
It's handled.

01:21:06.620 --> 01:21:09.500
她付了你额外的钱 让你收拾残局 对吧
She paid you extra to clean up loose ends, didn't she?

01:21:13.870 --> 01:21:15.500
现在我就是残局
And now I'm the loose end.

01:22:09.410 --> 01:22:10.330
很遗憾
I'm sorry.

01:22:13.120 --> 01:22:14.870
我知道他对你有多重要
I know how much he meant to you.

01:22:18.000 --> 01:22:22.080
我们之间的不完美如此美好
We had this... perfectly imperfect thing...

01:22:23.750 --> 01:22:26.540
时间磨不淡 距离冲不散
...that didn't fade with time or distance.

01:22:29.290 --> 01:22:33.200
知道有人爱你的一切
Knowing that someone loves everything about the way you are.

01:22:35.080 --> 01:22:36.410
好吧 除了我的双关笑话
Well, except the puns.

01:22:37.540 --> 01:22:39.160
萨姆讨厌双关
Sam hated those puns.

01:22:40.370 --> 01:22:41.200
是啊
Yeah.

01:22:43.540 --> 01:22:45.120
你知道吗 有那么一瞬间
You know, for a second there,

01:22:45.750 --> 01:22:47.990
我以为老天搞出这些破事
I thought that the universe did all this shit,

01:22:48.000 --> 01:22:50.660
这些糟心烂事
all this horrible shit,

01:22:51.950 --> 01:22:53.660
全是为了把我俩重新凑一块儿
just to bring us back together.

01:22:57.200 --> 01:22:58.370
我还很开心来着
And I was happy.

01:23:04.040 --> 01:23:05.120
挺疯狂的 对吧
Pretty demented, huh?

01:23:07.830 --> 01:23:09.910
刚发现我最好的朋友想杀了我
I just found out my best friend tried to kill me

01:23:09.910 --> 01:23:12.870
还想彻底搞垮西方民主
and wants to rip the heart out of Western democracy,

01:23:12.870 --> 01:23:16.080
所以现在有什么想法都算不上疯狂
so everything's being graded on a curve today.

01:23:19.950 --> 01:23:20.870
是啊
Yeah.

01:23:24.410 --> 01:23:27.410
随着决定北约命运的投票 30分钟后即将举行
...with a vote on the future of NATO set 30 minutes from now

01:23:27.410 --> 01:23:30.790
各国领导人纷纷公开宣泄对盟友的
and with world leaders openly expressing their outrage

01:23:30.790 --> 01:23:32.370
愤慨与怒火
and anger at their allies and friends,

01:23:32.370 --> 01:23:38.250
这个历经75载的军事同盟 此刻似乎已站在了解体的悬崖边缘
it seems imminent that after 75 years, NATO is on the verge of collapse.

01:23:39.620 --> 01:23:40.450
喂
Yes?

01:23:40.450 --> 01:23:41.700
总统女士
Madam President.

01:23:42.700 --> 01:23:44.330
谢谢你暂代我的职位
Thanks for keeping my seat warm.

01:23:44.580 --> 01:23:45.870
威廉 你是怎么...
Will? How did you...

01:23:45.870 --> 01:23:47.120
我马上就到
I'm coming in.

01:23:47.120 --> 01:23:48.330
告诉我你需要什么
Tell me what you need.

01:23:48.330 --> 01:23:50.370
我在得里雅斯特港
I'm at the Port of Trieste.

01:23:50.370 --> 01:23:51.330
让“野兽”来接我
Send the Beast.

01:23:51.330 --> 01:23:53.410
对了 科克 布拉德肖是内奸
Oh, and, Kirk, Bradshaw's behind this,

01:23:53.540 --> 01:23:55.830
别让她知道
so box her out.

01:23:55.830 --> 01:23:57.040
好的
O-Okay.

01:23:57.750 --> 01:24:02.870
我会尽量拖延北约的投票 请务必安全到达
Um, I-I'll hold off the NATO vote as long as I can, and-and just get here safe.

01:24:15.790 --> 01:24:16.620
总统先生
Mr. President.

01:24:17.700 --> 01:24:19.450
见到你可太好了
You sure are a sight for sore eyes.

01:24:20.250 --> 01:24:21.120
你先请
After you.

01:24:21.120 --> 01:24:22.040
谢谢
Oh, thank you.

01:24:37.250 --> 01:24:40.040
感谢各位 会议将于十分钟后开始
Thank you, everybody. The meeting will commence in 30 minutes.

01:24:43.200 --> 01:24:45.910
带他们去集合点 做好你的工作
Take them to the rally point and do your job.

01:24:46.040 --> 01:24:47.830
别再让我失望了
Don't disappoint me again.

01:24:49.830 --> 01:24:50.790
不是布拉德肖
It wasn't Bradshaw.

01:24:51.540 --> 01:24:52.410
是科克
It's Kirk.

01:24:52.410 --> 01:24:55.450
当然是副总统 总是副总统
Of course it was the vice president. It's always the vice president.

01:25:01.080 --> 01:25:02.250
科克抓到他们了
Kirk has them.

01:25:03.950 --> 01:25:05.910
别让他们到达北约会议现场
Don't let them get to NATO.

01:25:06.620 --> 01:25:08.950
但布拉德肖确实在和格拉多夫联系
But Bradshaw's communications were tied to Gradov.

01:25:08.950 --> 01:25:10.290
布拉德肖是个诱饵
Bradshaw was the decoy.

01:25:10.290 --> 01:25:11.990
科克掩盖了自己的电子足迹
Kirk covered her tracks.

01:25:12.000 --> 01:25:13.450
这叫应急方案
It's called contingencies.

01:25:13.450 --> 01:25:15.370
你有你的应急方案
You have your contingencies,

01:25:16.250 --> 01:25:17.250
我有我的
I have mine.

01:25:44.330 --> 01:25:45.620
有人追来了
We got company!

01:25:50.330 --> 01:25:51.500
开枪打他
Shoot him!

01:25:52.330 --> 01:25:53.540
开枪
Take the shot!

01:26:02.620 --> 01:26:03.870
该死 完了
Oh, sh-shit.

01:26:03.870 --> 01:26:05.200
- 去开车  - 好的
- Take the wheel! - Okay!

01:26:24.700 --> 01:26:26.040
好耶
Yeah!

01:26:40.200 --> 01:26:42.290
萨姆
- Sam? - Sam?

01:26:42.290 --> 01:26:44.120
稳住车子
Hold her steady!

01:26:44.120 --> 01:26:45.660
好的 没问题
Okay, no problem!

01:26:59.000 --> 01:27:00.080
你怎么还活着
How are you alive?!

01:27:12.500 --> 01:27:13.330
别激动
Easy.

01:27:13.330 --> 01:27:15.450
我只是保持冷静 继续前行
I just kept calm and carried on.

01:27:16.250 --> 01:27:17.540
去帮她 这里有我
Help her. I've got this.

01:27:19.500 --> 01:27:20.450
抱歉 伙计
Sorry, mate.

01:27:37.620 --> 01:27:38.540
开门
Open the door!

01:27:44.080 --> 01:27:44.910
很糟吗
Is it bad?

01:27:50.830 --> 01:27:52.950
- 我们要去哪  - 我来了
- Where are we going? - I got you.

01:27:54.080 --> 01:27:56.410
别第三次死在我面前好吗
Don't go dying on me a third time, okay?

01:27:59.450 --> 01:28:01.080
我腿上有把刀
Oh, there's a knife in my leg!

01:28:08.080 --> 01:28:10.080
等等 也许我们不该把它拔出来
No, wait, wait. Maybe we should leave it in.

01:28:10.080 --> 01:28:12.330
不不不
No, no, no, no, no, no, no, no, no, no, no!

01:28:14.500 --> 01:28:16.620
- 也没那么糟 - 很好
- Wasn't that bad. - Good. Okay.

01:28:25.000 --> 01:28:25.830
萨姆
Sam?

01:28:26.750 --> 01:28:27.950
踩油门
Punch it!

01:28:43.330 --> 01:28:44.330
趴下
Get down!

01:28:54.830 --> 01:28:56.000
我在盲开
I'm driving blind here!

01:28:58.660 --> 01:29:00.410
这里 卫星地图
Here! Sat view!

01:29:01.620 --> 01:29:02.580
很好
Nice.

01:29:06.450 --> 01:29:08.290
这辆蝙蝠车里还有其他玩具吗
Any other toys in this Batmobile?

01:29:14.290 --> 01:29:15.410
烟雾
Smoke!

01:29:19.160 --> 01:29:21.580
- 转 快转  - 这就转
- Turn. Turn. Turn. Turn! - I will. I will. I will.

01:29:45.040 --> 01:29:45.910
冰箱
The fridge!

01:29:46.040 --> 01:29:47.750
什么 要用零食干掉他们
What, are you gonna kill them with snacks?

01:29:50.040 --> 01:29:51.370
备用血液
Backup blood supply.

01:29:53.250 --> 01:29:55.250
接好了 该死的王八蛋
Take this, you bloody bastards!

01:30:11.660 --> 01:30:13.620
是“野兽”
That's the Beast. It's the Beast!

01:30:15.910 --> 01:30:17.410
他有火箭筒
He's got a rocket launcher!

01:30:17.410 --> 01:30:18.660
萨姆 敌袭
Sam, incoming!

01:30:49.410 --> 01:30:51.540
你已到达目的地
You have now reached your destination.

01:30:54.040 --> 01:30:55.660
从今晚午夜起
Effective midnight tonight,

01:30:55.660 --> 01:30:59.120
意大利将正式退出北约
Italy will be withdrawing from the NATO alliance.

01:31:00.370 --> 01:31:03.040
我们也代表法兰西共和国
On behalf of the Republic of France,

01:31:03.580 --> 01:31:04.950
正式退出
we withdraw as well.

