我怀着沉痛的心情宣布 尽管我已为维系此联盟付出
It's with a heavy heart, despite my most strident efforts

01:31:10.540 --> 01:31:12.490
不遗余力的努力
to hold this alliance together,

01:31:12.500 --> 01:31:14.540
我代表美利坚合众国
on behalf of the United States,

01:31:14.540 --> 01:31:16.450
宣布退...
I withdraw our...

01:31:16.950 --> 01:31:18.330
打住
Hold it right there!

01:31:23.870 --> 01:31:25.620
我代表英国...
On behalf of the United Kingdom...

01:31:25.620 --> 01:31:27.240
和美国...
And the United States of America.

01:31:27.250 --> 01:31:29.450
大家别情绪上头
...take it all down several notches, everyone.

01:31:29.450 --> 01:31:30.410
没错
That's right.

01:31:31.250 --> 01:31:33.040
我们可没那么容易被干掉
You're not getting rid of us that easy.

01:31:33.620 --> 01:31:35.790
这个联盟也休想说散就散
And we're not getting rid of this alliance that easy,

01:31:35.790 --> 01:31:38.790
因为我们都有自己的职责
because we all have a job to do.

01:31:38.790 --> 01:31:39.790
我明白
I get it.

01:31:40.370 --> 01:31:42.080
你们很羞愤 你们很愤慨
You're embarrassed. You're angry.

01:31:42.080 --> 01:31:45.660
但我们需要北约 我们需要合作
But we need NATO. We need partnerships.

01:31:47.290 --> 01:31:49.490
我们需要尊重彼此
We need to treat each other with respect,

01:31:49.500 --> 01:31:51.490
拥抱差异
embrace each other's differences

01:31:51.500 --> 01:31:54.120
寻求大同
and lean into our commonalities.

01:31:54.120 --> 01:31:58.490
向子孙后代传递一个信息 那就是我们在这里
To send a message to future generations that we were here.

01:31:58.500 --> 01:32:00.040
我们做了正确的事
That we did the right thing.

01:32:01.540 --> 01:32:03.500
首先要做的就是
And that starts by taking the fight

01:32:04.370 --> 01:32:06.160
向真正的敌人宣战
to the very real enemies we face.

01:32:07.160 --> 01:32:08.160
够了
There it is.

01:32:08.830 --> 01:32:10.370
这就是必然的结局
The inevitable conclusion.

01:32:11.370 --> 01:32:14.620
人民选出了个蠢演员 来当自由世界的领袖
The people elect a dopey actor as leader of the free world.

01:32:14.620 --> 01:32:16.750
这样他们的国家怎么可能存活呢
Of course their country can't survive.

01:32:17.700 --> 01:32:19.410
你就这样轻易达成协议了
And you just sealed the deal.

01:32:19.410 --> 01:32:21.410
这些人是我们的伙伴 我们需要他们
These people are our partners, and we need them.

01:32:21.410 --> 01:32:22.490
需要他们做什么
For what?

01:32:22.500 --> 01:32:25.410
我们自己种植食物 抽取石油 生产制造
We grow food. We pump oil. We manufacture.

01:32:25.410 --> 01:32:30.750
同时 我们还得派人去帮他们打仗
Meanwhile, we send our people to die in their wars.

01:32:31.250 --> 01:32:33.700
这不是合作关系
This is not a partnership.

01:32:33.700 --> 01:32:35.910
我们付出 他们只会坐享其成
We give, they take.

01:32:36.540 --> 01:32:37.950
但现在不是了
But not anymore.

01:32:38.660 --> 01:32:41.330
航班即将坠毁
The plane is going down.

01:32:41.330 --> 01:32:44.870
我们得先给自己戴上氧气面罩
We put the oxygen masks on ourselves first.

01:32:45.660 --> 01:32:48.160
- 反正这些都是虚假的联盟 - 虚假的联盟
- These are all false alliances anyway. - False alliances?

01:32:48.750 --> 01:32:50.660
看来你对此很了解啊
That's something you know a lot about.

01:32:50.660 --> 01:32:52.750
这是你最难过的点 对吗
That's what kills you most, isn't it?

01:32:53.370 --> 01:32:56.240
不是因为我是个比你更优秀的政治家
It's not that I'm a better politician than you'll ever be.

01:32:56.250 --> 01:32:57.790
而是因为我是比你更优秀的演员
It's that I'm a better actor.

01:33:10.410 --> 01:33:11.290
把他们全杀了
Kill them all.

01:33:16.250 --> 01:33:17.410
所有人趴下
Everybody, down!

01:33:25.410 --> 01:33:26.410
那边
Over there!

01:33:26.410 --> 01:33:27.620
快进来
Get in here!

01:33:28.410 --> 01:33:29.250
趴下
Get down.

01:33:51.830 --> 01:33:52.870
去干掉她
Deal with her.

01:34:07.910 --> 01:34:09.580
快点 我们该走了
Now! We should go now!

01:34:13.250 --> 01:34:14.580
那边 快走
That way!

01:34:14.580 --> 01:34:16.870
不 那边 快
No, no, no! That way! Go! Go!

01:34:44.620 --> 01:34:45.500
格拉多夫
Gradov!

01:35:00.080 --> 01:35:01.830
伙计们 快点 我们得走了
Guys, come on! We've got to go!

01:35:04.290 --> 01:35:05.120
萨姆
Sam!

01:35:05.120 --> 01:35:06.200
威廉
Will!

01:35:28.450 --> 01:35:29.540
诺埃尔
Noel.

01:35:29.540 --> 01:35:31.620
去追格拉多夫 我来搞定他
Get Gradov! I got this guy.

01:35:32.950 --> 01:35:34.080
她说她搞定
She said she's got it.

01:35:36.000 --> 01:35:36.830
走吧
Go.

01:36:25.450 --> 01:36:26.450
开枪打他
Shoot him?

01:36:50.120 --> 01:36:51.040
把枪拿起来
Get the gun.

01:37:03.950 --> 01:37:05.700
瞧瞧谁才是动作片主角
Who's the action hero now, huh?

01:37:11.950 --> 01:37:12.790
威廉
Will!

01:37:16.660 --> 01:37:17.580
可以上了吗
Good to go?

01:37:18.450 --> 01:37:19.830
这次别再只射墙了
Try not to kill the wall.

01:37:25.790 --> 01:37:27.450
我打中他了
I got him. I got him.

01:38:16.950 --> 01:38:18.620
他肯定在里面
He's got to be in here somewhere.

01:38:41.950 --> 01:38:42.870
我觉得他没子弹了
I think he's out.

01:38:43.660 --> 01:38:44.660
上
Let's dance.

01:39:05.040 --> 01:39:06.000
把枪扔了
Drop it.

01:39:10.000 --> 01:39:11.040
退后
Back up.

01:39:11.830 --> 01:39:12.700
退后
Back up!

01:39:25.830 --> 01:39:27.000
你已经无处可去了
There's nowhere to go.

01:39:28.080 --> 01:39:28.950
大结局了
It's over.

01:39:30.080 --> 01:39:31.410
这可不是我的结局
Not for me.

01:39:35.870 --> 01:39:38.580
该死 我们就这样让他跑了
Goddamn it! We're gonna let him get away?

01:39:39.370 --> 01:39:41.370
十年太久 必须现在抓住他
We can't wait ten years to get this guy.

01:39:43.160 --> 01:39:44.790
没错 十年太久
We're not waiting ten years.

01:39:46.620 --> 01:39:49.410
你还记得《水蟒2》的结局吗
Do you remember at the end of Water Cobra 2?

01:39:50.200 --> 01:39:51.870
你说你没看过我的电影啊
You said you never saw my movies.

01:39:51.870 --> 01:39:53.790
我说骗你的 我全看过
I know. I lied. I've seen them all.

01:39:54.580 --> 01:39:55.580
都是经典之作
They're classics.

01:39:55.790 --> 01:39:57.950
但最最震撼人心的一幕
But the one moment that really cut through them all

01:39:57.950 --> 01:40:01.620
是“水蟒”牺牲自己来拯救他的兄弟
is when Water Cobra sacrifices himself to save his brother.

01:40:04.580 --> 01:40:05.950
你知道我在说什么吗
You know what I'm talking about?

01:40:12.330 --> 01:40:13.870
数到三
We go on three?

01:40:18.160 --> 01:40:19.000
三
Three!

01:41:42.870 --> 01:41:44.160
我这个健身房强者如何
How's that for gym strong?

01:41:46.450 --> 01:41:47.450
嘿
Hey!

01:41:56.410 --> 01:41:58.700
“箭”出必有因
Everything harpoons for a reason.

01:42:17.120 --> 01:42:19.160
北约濒临解散两个月后
Two months after NATO nearly disbanded,

01:42:19.160 --> 01:42:22.620
该联盟在重建信任方面 迈出了令人鼓舞的进展
the alliance is making hopeful strides in rebuilding trust.

01:42:22.620 --> 01:42:26.200
德林杰总统与克拉克首相 在推行新型透明度机制中
President Derringer and Prime Minister Clarke have been crucial in these efforts,

01:42:26.200 --> 01:42:28.620
起到了关键作用
as new transparency measures are being implemented

01:42:28.620 --> 01:42:30.830
各方正逐步重拾协同共识
and there's a restored sense of cooperation.

01:42:30.830 --> 01:42:32.160
- 你的酒 - 多谢
- Here you go. - Cheers.

01:42:45.950 --> 01:42:46.790
真不错
Nice.

01:42:47.660 --> 01:42:48.750
你们俩要再续前缘了吗
You two gonna rekindle?

01:42:49.700 --> 01:42:50.830
我不知道
Uh, I don't know.

01:42:50.830 --> 01:42:53.660
她正在世界各地执行机密任务
She's halfway around the world on some covert operation.

01:42:53.660 --> 01:42:55.080
看看接下来怎么样吧
We'll see how it goes.

01:42:55.080 --> 01:42:56.830
还是有点复杂 知道吗
Still a bit complicated.

01:42:56.830 --> 01:42:59.040
只要让她多看优点 少看缺点
Well, just talk her out of the cons and into the pros.

01:42:59.040 --> 01:43:00.370
也许她会回心转意的
Maybe she'll come around.

01:43:00.370 --> 01:43:01.660
其实
Actually...

01:43:02.870 --> 01:43:05.080
你能帮我看看这条怎么回
you might be able to help me with this.

01:43:05.080 --> 01:43:07.910
“恭喜你支持率飙升
"Congratulations on your big bump in approval ratings.

01:43:07.910 --> 01:43:10.660
看来你的民调 也没你想的那么‘民掉’啊”
Guess you're not as poll-arizing as you thought."

01:43:10.660 --> 01:43:13.330
- 好吧 我们也用双关回她 - 好吧
- Okay, so now we got to hit her with a pun back. - Okay.

01:43:13.330 --> 01:43:17.540
这样吧...“确实还行 但和你比还是不够‘屌’啊”
Uh, it's, um, it's, uh... "That's nice, but it polls in comparison to you."

01:43:18.290 --> 01:43:19.160
你知道吗
You know what?

01:43:19.160 --> 01:43:21.660
我还是就回“谢谢”好了
I think I'm just gonna go with: "Thank you.

01:43:21.660 --> 01:43:23.620
“我想念你
I miss you.

01:43:23.620 --> 01:43:25.410
希望很快能见到你
Hope to see you soon.

01:43:26.160 --> 01:43:27.290
别中枪了”
Don't get shot."

01:43:28.830 --> 01:43:30.330
你猜怎么的 这回复太完美了
You know what? That's perfect.

01:43:31.870 --> 01:43:33.160
免得等下我忘了
Before I forget,

01:43:33.160 --> 01:43:36.250
两张哈里斯泰尔斯 华盛顿歌友会的票
two tickets to a meet and greet with Harry Styles in D.C.

01:43:36.830 --> 01:43:39.450
说真的 现在你是最酷的 萨姆大叔了
It's official. You are now the coolest Uncle Sam I know.

01:43:39.450 --> 01:43:41.200
谢谢 饿了吗
Thank you. You hungry?

01:43:41.200 --> 01:43:42.660
饿死了 有什么好吃的
Oh, I'm starving. What's good here?

01:43:42.660 --> 01:43:44.700
我给我们点了些吃的
I ordered us a little something.

01:43:45.540 --> 01:43:46.540
请慢用 先生们
Here you go, gents.

01:43:48.700 --> 01:43:50.080
好吧
Okay. All right.

01:43:51.290 --> 01:43:53.120
炸鱼薯条
Fish and chips.

01:43:53.120 --> 01:43:54.160
吃吧
Dig in.

01:43:55.160 --> 01:43:57.200
你们...什么 没有番茄酱
You guys, um, got any, uh, ketchup?

01:43:57.330 --> 01:44:00.040
没有 我们加醋
No. We do vinegar.

01:44:00.750 --> 01:44:02.290
这是薯条 又不是沙拉
Yeah, these are fries. This is not a salad.

01:44:02.290 --> 01:44:04.200
我的国家 我的调味品
Well, my country, my condiments.

01:44:05.830 --> 01:44:07.910
好吧 知道吗
Okay. Okay. You know what?

01:44:08.540 --> 01:44:10.870
等你来椭圆办公室的时候 我们得配番茄酱
Well, you come to the Oval Office, we're doing ketchup.

01:44:10.870 --> 01:44:13.700
一旦你改变主意 你就会被...
Once you see the light, you're gonna be stocking the, um...

01:44:15.120 --> 01:44:16.250
你的办公室叫什么名字来着
What the hell's your office called again?

01:44:16.370 --> 01:44:17.620
- 我的办公室  - 对
- My office? - Yeah.

01:44:17.620 --> 01:44:19.330
就叫我的办公室
It's called "my office."

01:44:20.410 --> 01:44:22.990
你们真的是很乏味啊
Boy, you guys are really afraid of spicing things up, huh?

01:44:23.000 --> 01:44:27.200
是啊 用颜色和形状来命名真的很辣
Oh, yeah. It's really spicy to name things after colors and shapes.

01:44:27.200 --> 01:44:29.790
- 你知道我的意思 -“我们该怎么称呼这个白房子
- You know what I mean. - "Hey, what should we call this white house?

01:44:29.790 --> 01:44:31.040
- 白宫 ” - 住嘴吧
- Mm, the White House?" - Don't.

01:44:31.040 --> 01:44:33.200
“这间办公室是椭圆形的 我们应该叫它什么
"Hey, this office is oval. What should we call it?

01:44:33.200 --> 01:44:35.200
- 我知道了 就叫椭圆...” -“椭圆办公室”
- I know." - The Oval Office.

01:44:35.200 --> 01:44:36.620
- 真辣啊 - 对
- Yeah, yeah. - That's real spicy.

01:44:36.620 --> 01:44:38.870
你有意见吗 去跟乔治华盛顿说啊
Hey, you got a problem, take it up with George Washington, okay?

01:44:38.870 --> 01:44:42.040
他在椭圆办公室 建成前100年就去世了
He died a hundred years before the Oval Office was even built.

01:44:42.830 --> 01:44:44.490
为什么非要跟我较真
Uh, why you gonna bust me on a technicality?

01:44:44.500 --> 01:44:47.410
- 较真来说 这不算较真 - 这只是无关紧要的细节
- Well, technically it's not a technicality. - It's an insignificant detail.

01:44:47.410 --> 01:44:49.990
不 这是事实 这才是需要较真的地方
No, it's a fact, which is exactly what a technicality is.

01:44:50.000 --> 01:44:52.740
你什么时候成为农民的  你要把笑点榨干了
When did you become a farmer? 'Cause you are milking this.

01:44:52.750 --> 01:44:56.160
真的吗 什么时候轮到 你这个羊奶头爱好者来说我了
Really? Says you, the sheep nipple aficionado?

01:44:56.160 --> 01:44:57.830
这事就不用再提了吧
I don't even think we need to talk about that.

01:44:57.830 --> 01:45:00.080
- 不想提这个吗  - 不想
- You don't want to talk about that? - No. No, we don't.

01:45:10.540 --> 01:45:12.200
我为民众吃枪子了吗
Did I take one for democracy?

01:45:12.200 --> 01:45:14.330
当然了 脑袋中了一枪
You bet I did. Right in the noggin.

01:45:14.330 --> 01:45:18.620
但谁会想到呢 这颗子弹正好击中
But who would've thunk it? This bullet hit at the exact spot where

01:45:18.620 --> 01:45:22.120
我当初因为烤架翻车事件 植入的金属板
I had the metal plate installed after my whole rotisserie grill debacle.

01:45:23.660 --> 01:45:28.910
要是当初打偏哪怕一纳米 我都没法在这喝“巴哈马妈妈”了
I mean, one nanometer either way, I am not here sipping this Bahama Mama.

01:45:28.910 --> 01:45:30.410
绝无可能 长官
No, sir.

01:45:30.910 --> 01:45:32.120
我是英雄吗
Am I a hero?

01:45:33.290 --> 01:45:35.950
当然 不定时跟总统和首相聊天时
Sure. Yeah, that's what the president and prime minister say

01:45:35.950 --> 01:45:38.950
他们都说我是英雄
whenever we talk on a semi-regular basis.

01:45:38.950 --> 01:45:42.410
是的 都是些关于内阁任命的小闲聊
And yes, there's some light chitchat about a cabinet appointment.

01:45:42.410 --> 01:45:43.490
没什么大不了的
No big deal.

01:45:43.500 --> 01:45:45.200
- 是啊 - 当然了
- Yeah. - Sure thing.

01:45:45.870 --> 01:45:46.830
不错的尝试
Nice try.

01:45:51.410 --> 01:45:52.660
我相信你
I believe you.

01:45:54.370 --> 01:45:56.910
很高兴认识你 科米尔探员
Nice to meet you, Agent Comer.

01:46:57.080 --> 01:47:00.160
国家元首